placeAddress: 60 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Craft House is my absolute favorite spot! The food is fantastic, the vibe is super comfortable and fun, and the service is excellent - friendly, attentive without being overbearing, and knowledgeable! Their mainstays are all excellent: popcorn chicken, chicken wonton tacos, smash burgers, chicken sandwiches, wings, and their special lamb burger all can't be beat! The sides are nothing to miss, either, with arguably my favorite fries, great mac and cheese, and that corn bread *chef's kiss*. Combined with top-tier local brews by Kills Boro, what's not to love?

placeName: Other Half Brewing - Rockefeller Center Taproom
reviewText:
Other Half's taproom is a no-brainer, must-visit for craft beer lovers in New York. This brewery is known for its innovative and tasty hazy IPAs, but also stouts and sours. The tap list changes regularly, so there is always something new to discover, from exclusive releases to beloved classics. Recommended (February 28, 2025) is the Triple Citra Daydream and the BA Banaverse.

The atmosphere in the taproom is modern and relaxed, with limited seating space. You can taste beers in different sizes of glasses, so you can try multiple styles (beerflight available). The staff is friendly and knowledgeable and is happy to help you choose between all the IPA options.

In addition to the draft beers, there are also cans and bottles to go, including limited editions, ideal for further enjoyment at home. Whether you're a seasoned beer connoisseur or just want to try something new, Other Half offers a top experience. An absolute must for craft beer fans in NYC!

placeName: Other Half Brewing - Rockefeller Center Taproom
reviewText:
Great beer selection but rude bartender by the name of Emma! It’s already challenging being a minority in these times and here you go making people more uncomfortable.

I Simply asked you to look at someone beer on the table, so that I can get a recommendation/idea from you as to what type of beer I should recommend to my friend. Basically looking to find something that my friend would be interested in drinking but you took something so simple and made an issue out of it, causing this whole scene and ultimately embarrassing me. It was a simple ask but you looked at me like I was stupid and just said “I am not looking over there because I won’t know what beer that is.” I didn’t expect you to tell me exactly what beer it was, but I was looking for the type of beer. It almost feels like you just had a point to prove after I asked you multiple times to look and my reason for asking. I asked for another person to help and you instantly replied “well it’s only manny and I here.” In any case, you ruin my experience. Lesson learned and I guess you won because that was my 2-3 time coming here and I will never come back after that embarrassment.

Shout out to you Manny.  I appreciate you stepping in and just simply trying to help and serve great beer. We need more people like you.

placeName: Other Half Brewing - Rockefeller Center Taproom
reviewText: I love otherhalf, they make great beer! However, the staff at this location and very unpleasant which makes me really not like going. There have been multiple instances where I've come and the staff seem as if they hate being there and serving customers. I understand having a long shift and that may be tiring, especially if your having a bad day. I think that's justified, everyone has bad days. But it's like this everytime I've gone. I try to be really patient with the staff because I know they're working hard. But there have been instances where I've asked what beers they have availability to go and been met with, "well you can scan that code or me and you can just keep talking..." personally I think that was a bit rude. I know that that I can scan the code and look to see, but there have been instance where I've requested what was available online, but they were out of stock. And besides that, I just found that to be a really rude response for no reason. I wouldn't write a negative review unless I really thought it needed to be said, but I legitimate dread dealing with some of the staff due to their attitude towards their customers.

reviewText: This place is the bomb! My husband and I went for the beer. Left with our stomachs full and very happy for such great service. First the Kills Boro IPA's are amazing. placeAddress: 60 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText:
Hadn't been here in about 5 years (last experience was "ok"). Went with the wife and kid-
There's no table service (the bartender is stuck doing double duty. He drops off your food, but didn't ask how is everything thing, do you need anything, etc). You order using a QR code, but still tip... The website that you use for ordering is simple to use, but the photos of the items are misleading.
The food seemed edible.. The menu options are uninspired and largely things that were unique to the area a decade ago (e.g. pastrami egg rolls, Mac & cheese balls, etc). Popcorn chicken was super dry. Mac & cheese was okay with bread crumbs but nothing amazing. Chicken and waffles serving was the size of a Dunkin Donuts sandwich. The French fries and Collard Greens were super, super salty. At home an hour and a half later all 3 of us had to urgently use the bathroom... Entré prices weren't crazy, but weren't a good value for the quantity or quality.
The dining area was clean- no sticky floors or tables-  a plus for a restaurant/bar. However, the bathroom needed help (broken seat, and thick dust covering the lights). I hope the owner/management accept this feedback as a call to step things up.

placeName: Other Half Brewing - Rockefeller Center Taproom
reviewText:
The first time I visited this taproom was during Christmas, and it was packed. Their beer was pretty good, but it was so loud and busy. I came back to NYC at the beginning of August and decided to visit again to get a better experience of the place.
I went on a Monday afternoon, there were two people working and about 10 customers. One employee was super friendly, the other clearly didn't want to be there, and even expressed this to me when he was cashing me out. While I was there a friend stopped in to visit him, they chatted non stop for at least 10 min at the bar while he completely ignored all of the other customers. Then chatted some more at the door before the friend left. If you don't want to be there, don't show or tell your customers, keep it to yourself.

After I cashed out and left I realized that I was over charged. I checked my credit card statement, then compared the charges to what my photos showed of the prices on the beer menu on the wall. Sure enough, I was overcharged by close to $10. I submitted a message on their website, which said I'd receive a response within two business days. After five business days of crickets I sent them a direct email. Three more business days passed with no response whatsoever, so I had to file a dispute with my credit card.
Why does a brewing company with locations in multiple states and countries have zero customer service?  Super disappointed, because their beer is pretty good.

My significant other and myself stopped by to try them on Saturday.  I was really impressed by the service and great food. Especially since I am allergic to garlic the chef came out to confirm and explained to me that most of the ingredients used has garlic. To my amazement he personally prepared my food. Outstanding I believe his name is Keith and our waitress name is Christy. Outstanding service and great prices. We will definitely go back.🥰🥰

My wife and I had a terrible experience at Miller’s Ale House. When we walked in, there was no one to greet us, and we had to search for a hostess. We passed by a bartender/server who saw us but didn’t acknowledge us. After walking into another room, we finally found a hostess, but she directed us to someone else who was on the phone. Instead of assisting us, he hesitated, then told us to wait a few minutes while he finished his call. This happened on March 9th Sunday afternoon 2:30pm. Whoever is the owner should pull up the cameras because you are losing business before people even try your food. At that point, we decided to leave. The lack of hospitality and customer service was unacceptable. We didn’t even get the chance to eat, and we won’t be returning. If we could leave 0 stars we would.

Whatever you do, don’t waste your time!!! If you want drinks, fine, don’t expect to eat dinner! You’ll get in. You’ll leave your name. They’ll tell you 15 minutes. Two hours Will go by. So we tell them take our number and call us We’re gonna go have a couple of drinks…  three hours later we were never called! Short staffed… not my Problem! Apparently the orders were coming in so quick for GrubHub or delivery that the kitchen couldn’t keep up with the orders so the people in the actual Vicinity are  Screwed . They know what they’re doing because They’re getting everybody to drink and they don’t even bring you a lousy piece of bread or some chips! I beg of you do not waste your time going there if you think you’re gonna eat!
When we came in to eat we waited for about 15 minutes and no one came to take our order worst service ever.
I didn't take any pictures but, we went the day after Valentine's.. and we keep forgetting that everything is delicious here.

On February 16th, 2025 Sunday around 8:50pm me and my son waited almost 5 minutes by the entrance to be seated. Unfortunately there was no one by the entrance . No hostess, no waitress. I had to call the restaurant to be seated. There were some workers as a hostess ( blonde woman) and waitresses . They were so nasty using all bad words all the time to each other. They were very loud and they were slapping each other. Please check your cameras between 8:50-9:30pm. Even one of the worker came up to them ask for help and they didn’t even care. Unfortunately it is very shame and disappointed having workers like them in the restaurant business. We were not the only one who was very uncomfortable with their attitude and reaction. Other customers who were sitting at the bar were also uncomfortable . The customers were sitting on the bench by the window were also uncomfortable. You have cameras in the restaurant. Check all these cameras and you could see it very clearly. I was in the restaurant business for a long time and we were never ever letting workers to act like them. They could have their meals on their break without making customers uncomfortable.
Just okay,  nothing wow with the food,
More expensive and hella worse than Applebees. Server is non existent
Good service, great food. Awesome time. I would recommend stopping by to eat here. Well worth the trip.
So we only orderd  appetizers and they were pretty bad,Applebee's blows this place away,kinda scary, the best part was the waiter I believe his name was val.
Very good service. Good food.
Food was good , but could have been hotter.

Had a wonderful time at millers! Our waitress MADISON was out of this world !!! in a good way. She was so amazing, she is definitely the it girl of millers! MADISON made sure we were so good. she is a gem like no other. Bathrooms were clean and pleasent inside. wonder atmosphere i felt like i was home. the mashed potatoes tasted like my moms, it was an emotional experience. Ask for madison you won’t be disappointed.

Went in at 10 pm after  work for a beer. Wide selection of  beer amazing  choices.  I went  with  Guinness, and it was  great.  Also, I got fish and  chips   purely  amazing  and fresh. I wasn't expecting this  at 10pm. Awesome  job for the  staff and cooks. I am amazed.
Brittany is the best!!

Update: I raised this review because I gave this place another try and the food was fantastic. Maybe they were just having an off night last time. It happens.

I wasn't happy with the food at all. I ordered chicken parm and a salad to go. The salad was mediocre. The chicken parm was undercooked and the breading came right off of the whole piece.  What bothered me the most was that they wrapped the garlic bread in aluminum and threw it in the container on top of the chicken parm. Not only do I think that's dirty, but of course when I grabbed it, ALL of the mozzarella from the chicken was lifted right off and stuck to the aluminum. The sauce also wasn't so good. The fettuccine Alfredo was decent but not great.
Place is great atmosphere for drinking having a great time
This place never lets me down! My ol’ reliable for a pick me up. Good food, good people, good times!
Miller’s ale house
Food was awesome. We all had the assobucco and it was cooked perfectly n fell off the bone. Chris our waiter was very attentive and polite. I would go there to eat for sure.
We were there late night after work . food came out fast and our Waitter was really  nice. The drink was great too.
Great service and cold beer
Food place to get something good to eat
They need to get better cooks. The meat was dry. Most of the other food was good. My wife and I wasn’t too happy. I better off this going to the outback.
Great experience all around with cheap food.

The prices went up a little, portions are smaller, the menu has been condensed. My only complaint as far as the taste of the food goes is, take it easy on the salt on the fries. Our waitress was outstanding, that made the dining experience good.

Awful experience. Watched food sit on the window for over a half hour before it was brought to other people eating. Cancelled food order because of it and staff gave attitude after acknowledging they knew what was happening. That was not the worst part though, I had sat at the bar for 2 and half hours watching a basketball game and with 23 seconds left in double overtime the bar manager stated they were turning off the TV's with still over 40 people in the bar. Crazy they consider themselves a sports bar  and they should be truly embarrassed by this. Will never go back and have dedicated time to spreading news about what kind of place this is. BUMS.

I’ve eaten here plenty of times food was good this most recent time today at 7:15 was when I decided I could never go back me and my family were out to eat my cousin who is allergic to cheese got a burger with cheese even after ordering it with allergy in mind no resolution the rest of our meal all food that left that kitchen was absolutely disgusting I never complain or leave reviews but this had to be addressed the manager and server both said nothing after I addressed this with them i paid 100$+ for food that could not be eaten contact I had at this restaurant showed they had no care whether my service was good or bad which is the fastest way to eliminate customers such as myself that live in the area I feel bad for who owns this establishment because it will surely see a decline with people running it that don’t care about the customers

Our server was awesome which made up for the food. I will only speak on my choice. Zinger Mac and Cheese. The Zinger was great however the Mac and Cheese was wanting...to be better. Not enough cheese. You know when you have anything cheesy you look for the string of cheese when you bring the food from the plate to your mouth?  It wasn't there at all. They could have fooled me and used Velveeta box M&C and I would have been okay.

They really need to clean their booths and their bathrooms. The bathroom smelled and had trash on the floor and when I was seated in my booth there was food in the seat and rolled up paper on the floor. The server act as if she didn't see it. But this is something that you might have happened when you go late into the place They do have good dishes.

Great food especially the zinger's and the chicken quesadilla. Wonderful staff they're helpful and caring. Of course it's a family place but also a sports bar, lots of televisions to watch every sports channel. It even has a section where you can have an event, which I had one a few months ago. It was a great time. My family loved the place. I'm always in Miller's Ale house once a month. Go there and enjoy!!
Not the best
Good food and plenty of games on to watch
Everything was great! Food and service was excellent! Husband ordered the Pork Osso Buco and it was awesome!
Good food

What a wonderful experience guess they know it's tough to keep people coming back but they did a great job our server was so on the ball she kept coming back asking if everything was good the kitchen forgot my mac and cheese and the manager brought it to us all of our food was hot and fresh great experience.

Expensive for simple food.

Went there with a employee yelling at a customer. She then went on a rampage in the kitchen yelling at people. Hilarious...yet unprofessional.
Food was ok, service mediocre, host rude.

Featuring FRANCISCO, ELISSA & JOSEPH - Miller’s is an amazing experience.

Staff is, to me, as important as the food when I’m going out for some casual dining. Whoever did the hiring at this restaurant knows what they’re doing.

I’ve only been here three or four times, but I can swear to you that it’s worth your while.

Chicken fingers (they call them something else) are delicious. Burgers are fantastic. Mac and cheese. Giant Brownie Sundae. There are probably a lot more that I could mention, but I’m in a food coma right now.

Professionalism and conviviality are important important important.

Great place.
I ordered as soon as I walked in, and the server took her time getting the food. The chicken meal was dry, there was no seasoning, and it looked like it was not prepared well at all. This place sucks
Everybody was very polite, friendly, and very accommodating.

Went There today was served by a Hannah. Not a fan of the new management. The staff was ok. Definitely wont be coming back. The manorial staff has go to go. Prefer the old managers. They knew how to run a business. What happen to them? I’ll be taking my business to Tommy’s Tavern where I feel warm and welcome. 🤗

Service is great Kristi is always so pleasant and very good at putting a smile on someone’s face a very beautiful woman and always makes the visit enjoyable .i try to come at least once a week and love the place and set up. Thanks for making an experience very enjoyable Kristi .
There was only one staff member serving the customers. I had to go in and inform them that I have a curbside order.
Bigger than what I expected, service was great food was good if you're looking for something to change up the routine this spot will do it
Food was not what it use to be quality has gone down hill and to offer a steak that's paper thin  for 26 dollars I could have put 2 tooth picks in it and some strings  and flew it like kite ....

This is the worst food I ever ate. I ordered a card, fish and chips. It was disgusting. It was all breading no fish and it came back to me and ice cold no tartar sauce, lemon and ketchup. It was the worst food ever
Nice place with a good tap selection. While they have food, it's not a full menu, but go for the drinks.
Sweet staff, great beer selection, and chill atmosphere! Appreciate this space :)
Great selection, chill atmosphere, friendly bartenders
One of the friendliest and warm spaces to go to.
Absolutely love this spot, honestly some of the most attentive and kind staff around. Great frequent local and the beer selection is some of the best in the neighborhood. Keeps us coming back!
A hidden gem! don't miss out on the patio in the way back. bartender let us try like 4-5 beers each without even seeming annoyed! will be back. good for groups.

This sweet bar is the best around! My partner and I recently had our little wedding party here and I cannot speak highly enough about the drink selection, ambience, or INCREDIBLE owners and staff. Definitely a favorite and we will be going back for years to come.
Great beer place with garden, highly recommended if you want to bring kids. Food was really good, the cheese sandwich was so tasteful
Always a great time! The staff is awesome and the beer assortment is phenomenal!
Very warm and inviting environment, friendly staff and good beer/food....
Lovely staff and really beautiful patio in the back :) also great beer selection!
Wan  of the  best beer in Brooklyn.
LOVED IT FIRST TIME HERE!! AHMAZING
Beer in heaven
Pro: cheese melts. Con: Bartender is not attentive.
Really nice place, really nice staff - good selection of beer too
The friendliest staff!
Lovely cider options!
Great addition to the neighborhood! Owners and other staff are super friendly and they always have a great selection of beer on draught and for takeaway. Nice backyard for the warmer months!

Great local bar. Staff was friendly and the atmosphere was great. Got pretzel and tots to go with my beer. Was worried about the tots they looked under fried but it was really crispy and recommend for a small snack. Got a lager which was really good and they have good variety of beers and cider.
Love their craft beer!! We were celebrating bartenders day there :)
10/10 every time. They’ve got tons beer styles and everyone that works there is awesome. Couldn’t recommend enough.
Craft beer pub serving delicious beers by very friendly bartender. Lovely backyard with plenty of seats and brick-wall surrounding.
We were visiting family and stopped by for lunch. The food and staff were great. Next time we are in town, we'll be back.  Thanks.

Our waitress Bri was a delight and check in on us frequently and hilarious 😂. That’s cocktail 🍸 🍐 Pear martini is a great choice which I must say compliment the meal of choice and many A+ Recommendation which she knows her meals and we was pleased as she kept us intune with preference as well..
Food is good, but what stands out the most is the care and attention to detail of the service. Amazing staff 👏

I've been on the hunt for the ultimate sports bar with a trifecta of awesomeness: killer grub, top-notch brews, and the holy grail of onion soup. And, baby, I've found it! 🏆🍺🍴 This place is the real MVP, serving up a menu that's a slam dunk, a beer list that's a home run, and an onion soup that's a grand slam! 🤩
Love the food here! I come here occasionally and the food and service is always exceptional. Definitely a great place to get food and the vibe is always so chill.
Food was great!

These wings come from an animal that is the tiniest thing that could possibly be called a “chicken”. So small! Skimpflation :( and $11.99 for 6 miniscule wings. The Korean BBQ sauce was tasty and service was good.

We ordered two prime rib dinners.
When we went to eat it it was like rubber. You needed a saw to cut into it. Disgusting!
Couldn’t eat it. Went in the trash.
Will never go back there again.
I don’t know how they could serve that.
Food is good for the money. Val our waiter was awesome 👍🏾... Definitely a place I'd go back to...
Food was OK. Didnt order anything elaborate and it took forever to come out.

Lovely place, very welcoming, warm and calm atmosphere. Staff is super friendly, the back garden is spacious and really pretty. The place is spotless and very well taken care of. Excellent selection of beers. Mulled wine is delicious 👌 Nice gem, súper recommendable!
Great selection!
Maximally pleasant ambience
Great selection & staff. Love the vibe and board games!
Great currated selection of beers.
Exactly the kind of place I want to sit and catch up with friends over a beer. Great people, great beer selection, great patio!
Great staff, tasty beer, variety of party and long board games, patio at the back.

I think I'm being overly picky, but for a place with such a great focus on great beer, I wanted more than "bodega snacks" for food options. Don't get me wrong, I love Cheezits, but I rather kettle chips to Ruffles. But as for the beer, the real focus, it is a great selection and the staff is great. With different potato chip options, this would be 5 stars, and I'm really probably being unfair. 🤷
They helped me host my girlfriends birthday party and it was a great time, we had such a blast!
Great selection, knowledgeable staff

Very nice place. Very good beer list. Very nicely air-conditioned inside. Very spacious and dog friendly back patio. Very beautifully painted signage/window by Travis Signs. Very enjoyable. Will come back, very often, I hope.
Great bar, great staff. Much needed addition to the neighborhood!
whaaaaat a place WOW, came here for a 30s group hangout and had the best vibe, def recommend and will be back. Say hi to Josh for me 😂

Great space. Nice beers. Nice staff. But it’s one of those places where the neighborhood people bring their screaming children - adults hanging inside while one of them gets volunteered to oversee said group of screaming children in the back yard. The place is frequented by the kind of people who upon seeing that their kids are ruining an otherwise perfectly nice pub for you love to then get in your face to profusely apologize. Why people say Brooklyn, specifically Park Slope, sucks in a nutshell.

A great addition to the neighborhood! A well-curated beer list featuring (but not limited to) local breweries; friendly staff who are eager to help; and a comfortable and inviting space to chat, relax, play games, work, or do whatever else you want to do while enjoying good beer.

They also have a well-stocked fridge of cans and bottles to go!
Wonderful little cozy spot to try craft beers and bring home some.
Quality beers, vistas, snacks abide. Just the right amount of crowded, always.

So happy this opened! A very nice selection of draft beers, with cans to purchase up front. The bartenders are extremely friendly as well, and knowledgeable of you want to talk shop about craft beer. Would definitely recommend this place to beer nerds or people who like a chill place to drink in the neighborhood.
The perfect beer bar and shop!
Lovely outdoor space, great beer selection!
Great beer, nice local place, friendly staff. Great backyard patio with picnic tables. Outdoor area is dog friendly. Tuesdays has trivia!
Great place with a knowledgable and friendly team. Very much looking forward to using their backyard this summer. Very solid draft and bottle/can beer selection.
Cozy atmosphere and amazing selection!
Great selection of beer
Great vibe, solid selection of beers on tap, very spacious. Then when you are on your way home you can pick up some cold ones for the road from their selection of beers to go.
Similar to Beer Witch, but with a significantly wider selection of beers in cans. Plus they have the back yard which is a game changer.

Long overdue and welcome addition to the neighborhood (parents drink beer too!).  Amazing beer selection that will just get better over time.  Doesn't quite feel lived in yet, but I look forward to helping it get there.  The owners and staff are super friendly.
Great craft beer selection. Cans and draft

We went to catch the Oscars the last night of the soft open—wow! The team has done an incredible job putting this spot together. The beer selection is on point, with a respectable range of cider, wine, and non-alcoholic alternatives.

This place is the living room extension that Park Slope desperately needed. Can’t wait for the official open in a couple days!

One of the best breweries in NYC.

The blood orange IPA is amazing.  All of the cocktails, wines and beers are NYC made.  Live music on the regular.

You can have food delivered to Flagship and I highly recommend Pier 76 pizza.

Very family and dog friendly.

Popped in for some beers and food having got the midtown ferry over

Beer fantastic - food not available until 5 but pizza delivery recommended which was also brilliant. Happy to be eaten in the bar. Some games shuffle board.

Well worth visiting from the outlet
I had so much fun trying out the non alcohol options with the daytime bartender. He and the brewmaster were super nice. The space is warm and inviting. I’ll definitely be back!

Been here multiple times. Always something going on. Cornhole night, comedy night, trivia, etc. Homebrews are really great. Parking lot across the street. Close to shopping at the outlets and to the ferry.
Nice place. Great atmosphere. Beer is cold and good.
Ryan, the bartender, provided exquisite service.   I also had a chance to meet the brewer Doug, who provided a great lesson on the craft brewing process.   This is the center of great beer on SI.

Flagship Brewing Company is a decent spot to try a beer on Staten Island (also very near the ferry departures area). They have a number of beers, but I thought many of them were very similar (not a lot of variety in beet types, lots of lagers, etc.). They do, however, also have a nice cocktail list. And the have games like shuffleboard, and it looks like a good place to host events (they have them often, the men behind the bar said).
nice place friendly staff

We hosted a Friday night welcome event for our wedding at Sound + Fury Brewery and it was the perfect choice. We worked with Natalie, who was absolutely incredible - she and her team handled everything. They helped us build the menu, handled all staffing, and helped with audio set up. As our vision changed and the event grew bigger, they worked with us to adjust and made sure we had everything we needed. We can't recommend them enough for hosting events. The food was good (especially the pizzas), their beers are fun, and the ambiance is great. They even customized the little sign outside the brewery for us - it was so sweet! Natalie was a super-star.

So it seems that Circa rebranded and is now Sound + Fury with only one noticeable change, the service was much improved since my first visit a long time ago. That visit was so miserable I swore I wouldn't go back but a friend convinced me to try it again so we did.

First the good; the place is still beautiful with a large space and is very welcoming overall.

Now the bad;
1) The bar stools, while comfortable the majority are broken to some degree and slightly tilt on way or another and this is the actual top part of the stoll not a case of it rocking on an uneven floor.
2) The beer, it feels that the brewmaster is afraid of letting a beer reach its full potential, I found the beers to all be lacking in potential. They seemed like the fermentation process was stopped early or they were watered down to lower the ABV. The bartender told me the owner/brewmaster doesn't like high ABV beers, and that is fine but don't reduce quality for a lower ABV. I love a good session a beer and English Mild with a sub 4% ABV but those are still full of flavor. Even the black lager, which is historically a favorite style of mine was barely drinkable.

As for the food we didn't eat but the menu looked good and the few dishes that we saw did look good, but I am not sure I will be back to try the food as their are just so many better breweries to give my money too for better beer!

Brewpub, Arcade, and Feather bowl courts! Randolph Beer is an experience. Located down the street from the F at York, this spot blends industrial Brooklyn grit with retro arcade nostalgia. Think pinball, air hockey, and classic games alongside pour-your-own beer taps, so you can sample at your own pace.

My favorite beer: Stoop Kid – A traditional French saison with phenolic yeast aromatics, balancing peppercorn spice and citrus brightness. Crisp, complex, and perfect for sipping between arcade battles.

Food Standout: Corn Off The Cob – A messy, delicious mix of cotija, aioli, onion, red pepper, corn, and cheeto dust. Snack game = strong.

Bonus: In warmer months, the rooftop opens up for even better vibes.

If you’re into craft beer, vintage games, and a killer atmosphere, Randolph Beer is a must visit.

Just a comment about games pricing:  Randolph made the classic mistake for a commodity seller.  You make your money on volume not price. Set the game prices at the market and people will play more.  Set them over market and they play less.

This makes even more sense when you’ve already adopted a credit system because people buy more credits than they need when they are priced fairly. Seriously: margins don’t matter when your volume sucks.

ALL YOU NEED TO KNOW IS FEATHER BOWLING FOLKS! How often in this life do you get to experience a brand new activity/game that you have never ever played before? Feather Bowling is EXTREMELY rare like there are maybe 2 or 3 other places You can play Feather Bowling and none of them are anywhere near here! It’s an amazing sport! They have 2 lanes of Feather Bowling’s signature half pipe lanes that as many as 6 people (3 per team ) can roll wheels (not balls more
Like cheese wheels made of wood) wheels rolling them down the half pipe and seeing which team can get there wheels closest to the Feather , there it is. Which stands at each end of the( same
Length lanes as 10 pin bowling length lanes I think*) and also unique each team
Throws ALL its wheels before the other team and this changes the strategy to one of building defenses. It’s just awesome and fresh as hell cause nobody has done it before , believe me , go impress someone and take em here. Nobody knows about me this awesome game unless u r in Detroit , Montreal or Belgium really, cause it’s a Flemish game originally. Anyways everybody please go go go and support this place and u won’t be disappointed , it’s awesome  and new and fun! Thank You now NYC really has everything. 🎉🎉❤️🙏🏽

Apparently the euros don't have much value for these people who work in this place ;)

Walked across the Brooklyn bridge and we decided we wanted some cold brews. Wow this beer is good! Especially the pride punch, that was my favorite. The rooftop opens after 4:00 I was told so, we’ll definitely be back to check that out!

I like this place and often times, midday during the week, the service is good - but those crazy fun weekend days, it doesn’t really roll right. The draught beer by card is bad bc of foam and tapping issues - I like the vegan choices and the beer is interesting!

Was here on a Tuesday afternoon to watch Euro 2024 - they do not turn on the tv sound and keep playing the music even after we asked.
The whole place was filled with people only watching the game. Do not recommend for game watching!

Rooftop is only open Thu - Sun .
Best roof top, great activities and vibe .

Do not go here! Very let down! NOT FOR TOURISTS!

Staff  - African American worker stole phone when charging and when questioned he refused to help and denied completely. Manager did not even offer to check cameras. BE AWARE!
Great pinball playing experience! Feather bowling is a plus.
Incredible space with awesome beer! Great self serve wall and great service. Reasonably priced especially for the area! The waffle fries are truly special
Very cool place with lots of pun themed beers to choose from. Chill vibe and some interesting old school arcade games

We really enjoyed the vibe of this bar, but what really stood out was the level of service we received. We were trying out a beverage that we had never tried before.  Staff member Levi noticed that my girlfriend reacted aversely to the drinks we received. He immediately jumped into action and offered alternatives- Without us even asking. It was done thoughtfully, and in such a friendly manner that it left quite a positive impression on us. If you go there and get Levi as your server, you will be in good hands.

This place is great. It's got a fun ambience, a great beer selection, a bunch of TVs and super nice staff. The burger I had was pretty meh, but the tots, pretzel and chicken bowl were pretty good. Some of the logistics are confusing. It was difficult finding the rooftop. It was also a bit complicated to order. QR codes on the table requesting to order from the site, but then the bartender told us that we could've ordered with him. Some additional signage might be helpful. All in all, we had a great time and I'll definitely be back.
Great spot for a little lunch at the outdoor patio. 🤗 Was able to bring my puppy too!!
food was surprisingly good! A million types of beers on tap, and they have plenty of space and games to play. Great for large groups and you can reserve a space.
Fantastic choice of beers! The place was just a bit loud...

I should be clear. I’m leaving this review for the quality of the beer. Seems like a very fun place to play games. The beer however is pretty subpar. With breweries like Other Half, Grimm, Finback etc. around, this brewery has to step up the quality of the beer. The hazy IPA tasted like some of my early homebrewing attempts. None of the things you might expect from a hazy other than being cloudy. The German Pilsner had no recognizable qualities of a German Pilsner. Sorry to be a meanie, but I’m a local and I wish some other nerdy beer person had left this review for me to see. If you are looking for a good local pint, this isn’t it. If you’re looking for games and instagramable decor you’ll probably like it.
Really unfriendly to dog owners
They let people reserve the room with the bathrooms. So one bathroom for like 50+ people. Staff very dismissive and unhelpful. Food is mediocre except the chicken tenders which are very good

I used to love coming here before they raised their pinball prices, but until they charge a normal rate for pinball I won’t be back.

Honestly, the bar is great, but I’m a pinball player and nothing about this place justifies paying MORE THAN DOUBLE the going rate for a pinball game. Most bars charge $1 per game or $3 for 4 games. Randolph charges $2 for a game with no bulk discount!

The space is pretty small but has such a fun vibe.  Small selection of arcade games, but it's easy to have a good time even by yourself. You get your tokes from the bar tender where you can get some reasonably priced drinks. The food area is on the other side with more seating. I just got what I assumed to be a quick chicken tenders and fries, but it took a bit long, but I understand that it was relatively crowded. Sadly, the french fried were as hard as sticks and not enjoyable
Good food and beer, service is okay but they could be more helpful.
Beers are outta the world..
Came and left. This is a daycare with beer. Kids running amok.
Awesome place to hang out with friends and play games! They have feather bowling and arcade games. The staff were so friendly and Matthew was so welcoming. Will definitely come back!
Such a Fun and Cool place to have a Good time! They have an amazing quantity of Beers, the Steak Skewers are a MUST, so do yourself a favor and request them, they are Delicious 😋

My buddy and I came to Randolph on Saturday night to have some dinner and drinks. The space is huge, half of it’s like an arcade and the other half a bar to chill. We decided to chill first then play some games. We were greeted by Ruben and Duke and they were super knowledgeable and hospitable. The food was amazing and Ruben and Duke made sure we had everything we needed and made sure we weren’t thirsty! I strongly recommend this place for those who want to hang out or are on a first date and want to impress their partner!

Supper: Cool place to hang out with friends. I love the atmosphere and the self-service for beer 🍺 Big like👍
My favorite Beers are Fruit Beer,  American IPA, and German Pilsner 😋

I wouldn't say I liked the pizza bread - too much gravy, but the chicken nugget was great.
The atmosphere was great and the service was very friendly unfortunately food was mediocre at best and the beer generic and boring.
Excellent food.
The food was not tasty so I had a lot left over. Tater Tots were edible. The atmosphere is particularly bad. I don't want to go again.
Great place to have a drink after work, or to play some arcade games with friends.
Nice place to have a drink with coworkers after work .
Love the atmosphere and the place. It is usually pretty empty even though the place is dope including on Friday and Saturday nights. Many games are available and the loaded nachos are amazing!
Great place, great beer selection.
They have a "no child policy" even if it's a baby that can't walk .. doesn't make sense
The taproom was a great space, and beautiful view. Enjoyed seeing the brew system right there as well! Beers were good and the pizza is ordered through QR code

OG OH! The best selection of collaborations and fancy guest beers (including from my town, Austin, recently). Plenty of to-go, although they don't keep it out where you can window shop. Decent merchandise selection. Smaller than other OH locations I've visited, but similarly cool vibe.
Loved this place. Great vibe, friendly staff and awesome beers. Need to buy new games though, load of bit were missing.
Awesome brewery. Elite IPAs
Other Half takes its place among the greatest breweries in the country, maybe even the world. A destination for beer lovers from all walks of life, Other Half is sure to please everyone.

1/5/25 Here again which we enjoy. Shocked at how many little kids are here meaning toddlers one learning to walk in a brewery sort of funny! Lots of babies. Only a handful of us are adults which I guess means the parent need to drink. You can still bring in pizza or if needed McDonalds from across the street. Delicious beer today including the snowbirds 8

Here in Brooklyn right now. Beautiful Sunday afternoon. The doors are open, the delicious beer is flowing, and we have via Roma pizza. How wonderful. The staff offers their full explanation of the beers available for sale and cans and bottles for pick up. They even sell their logo on shirts and hats. Love the vibe!

Just tried Other Half’s All Citra Everything Double Dry Hopped Imperial IPA, and wow—it’s a tropical burst of mango, pineapple, and citrus. Super smooth, juicy, and not too bitter. At 8.5%, it’s way too easy to drink. If you love Citra hops, this one’s a no-brainer. Other Half crushed it!
My favorite Brooklyn brewery. Great selection of beers! With a specialization in awesome IPAs.
Great brewery with helpful staff and industrial warehouse aesthetic. Honestly can’t go wrong with your beer choice here if you’re a fan of NEIPAs

So i visited this brewery on centre st in Brooklyn... yep,  they know how to make beer! They definitely have hazy ipa's dialed in. They offer other beer styles and all are exceptional. Unfortunately I have only one picture because I was enjoying the beer too much!

Awesome spot! Other Half is known for their great IPAs so it was nice to actually visit the original brewery location. They had an incredible sour on tap as well. We ordered a few tasters so we were able to try a variety. Also noted they had a few cocktail offerings for those who might prefer cocktails over beer. Nice atmosphere. Friendly staff. Quite a few friendly dogs too! We were there early enough in the day to snag a table, but the place was pretty busy by the time we left. They also had a grill set up for a few food offerings (hot dogs, tacos, etc). Can’t wait to visit again next time we’re in the area.
Best spot to drink hazy bois under the BQE. Friendly staff, great merch, chill vibes.
Cool place, friendly staff and large selection of beers. But too many IPAs for my taste
Yes, finally made it to the source and beers delivered on taste and the Brooklyn under the bridge vibes are banging. LAD vs NYM too?!
Very cool laid back vibe. Dogs and infants and craft brews. Come one, come all and drink high quality craft beers. There was a pop up bespoke Dumpling Station when I was there.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText:
Staten Island Best Brewery!

Island Vibes !

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Come for the beer stay for the food! Food is delicious here!!

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Kills Boro Brewing Company is one of a couple breweries in the area, with a slightly different vibe than the others. They have a decent bar food menu, and more variety in their beers. Seating is more plentiful and the outdoor area is nicer, with ~10 or so picnic tables, a couple couch seating areas, and all partially shaded. If you're looking to try a new beer this is a good spot!

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText:
Amazing food, Amazing service, I haven’t tried beers because I am sober but my colleagues guaranteed they are amazing too.
Wonderful experience in my first visit at staten island.
Thank you so much.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Food was really great. Had the brisket. Beer also hit the spot. Glad to have stumbled upon this gem

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Everything great. The craft beer is very good and the food too. We have ordered pastrami, brisket and Smash burger and everything was delicious. It has surprised us. Great service. He has recommended us and treated us wonderfully. A place to come without a doubt on Staten Island!!! Thank you!

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: jerrold was super nice and great service

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Lovers of IPA, DIPA AND TIPA, Take the FREE ferry to Staten Island, walk 10 on Bay Street, turn left on Victoria street and right on Van Duzer street and you are there! CRAFT HOUSE. Great service and great beer. A terrace on the street, a patio with sofa, the food is classic and successful and the beer incredible and the music just enough to make an X generation cry with happiness. Finally something to do in Staten Island.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Good beers and also many delicious appetizer options! Especially the wings and the empanada!

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Ate here a few years ago, it was great. In 2024 came here one time had the popcorn chicken, 2nd time had the Pastrami egg rolls. Both times the food was mediocre. Beer and service are great but I cant keep getting let down. Is this place declining?

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText:
Another great microbrewery that fills growlers.  The place is a hidden gem. The Ferry Beer is a nice choice if one got off the boat at St. George Terminal.

Their food is also great and it's certain that one will pair nicely with one's meal.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Had dinner with my brother who was in from Connecticut. Food was very good. I had chicken and waffles. Loved it. Great craft beer. Highly reccomend this place.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Great vibe and friendly.  Oh and the beer was on point too.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText:
Beer good.
Food, like the brisket or the pulled pork super dry. Wanton saw a bit to much oil…

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Nice beer selection. Relaxing atmosphere. Staff are friendly, attentive, and have suggestions on beer selections.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Fun spot, chill outside in yard have a drink or their own draft beer. Inside cool vibe, with DJ. Attentive staff.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: This brewery was hosting a birthday party when I arrived but I managed to find a small seat in their beer garten to sit and enjoy my beers. Their beers were solid, not especially memorable, but it was nice to sit outside and look at the various lights and wall art.

Don’t really get this place. Food is solid, bartenders are great, and games are fun after a few rounds. But it’s often empty. I’m not sure hosting family day on Sunday with a handful of kids running around instead of running the sound and some specials for NFL playoffs, March Madness, etc is a good way for the GM to maximize check value,  but what do I know. Also, randomly closed sometimes. Dumbo/DTBK desperately needs a lively sports bar, just wish this could be it.

Nice bartenders, some of the best and most accessible for varied diets bar food I've ever had. Best hummus I've ever had and they have such great variety!!

Definitely coming back

Nice place to hang out with friends or coworkers. Big space with multiple sections. Have games available to play. Drinks from the bar were good. They have I believe two bars, one on each side.  Food came in big portions and was tasty. Overall had a good experience here
My wife and I visit Randolph every single time we’re in NY. The staff, the beer, the vibe make it one of our favorite places!
Fun spot for groups. Pay as you pour system is absolutely infuriating but once upon a time cool novelty. Order at the bars.

There is a rooftop bar, entrance is outside the building. They have really good cocktails and finger foods. They also have an option for your cocktail to be served in a pitcher to share! A bit pricey but for the drink/food quality and the view? Worth it!

Here scan the QRS code and order all their beer I had the Orange you lovely beer and hubby got a caramel apple beer they were so good and strong we order the chicken tendies thanks for Julian that helps us with the beer choices we wanted.
For me Randolph will always be the place I know I will have the best time and the best drink. 5 stars, and really more.

I get excited to go there as I love games. I have brought my networking acquaintances, classmates, and friends there. Perfect place to hangout, play games, and have a beer. The food selection is great for snack. The menu is international with a bit of a lack of focus but the food taste good. Highly recommend.

This is great. It is a great place to stop and relax and enjoy a drink and some games.  Upstairs, there is a bar and lots of fun games to play.  I would definitely put this place on your list to visit while in the city.  Great location between Brooklyn Bridge and Manhattan Bridge.

Better food than I expected.  Fried chicken sandwich was quite good. But the bartender was remarkably unhelpful and
should not be in service industry.  Some of their game reservation policies are inane.
Amazing bere! Must Enjoy ❤️🗽
Always a great time! Wonderful smell of malt hits you as you walk up the street.
Great place and selection of beers
These guys knock INEIPAs out of the park, outstanding juicy brews served up by friendly, welcoming staff 👌🍻
Beer!!! Favorite brewery in town!!!

Stopped by on the Monday of Labor Day weekend, expected it to be busier based on previous visits, I generally try to only come here on weekdays to avoid the crowds.  It was the right kind of busy, you could get a seat but all of the tables were taken creating a comfortable energy, plenty of dogs too, which always improves the atmosphere.  We came because it was Trillium & friends week, had the Every Gazillion ever, Like like whoa whoa and the sweet potato fries.  The beer, as usual, was excellent but more on that elsewhere.

Cream of the crop for beer in Brooklyn. Sometimes mid-week releases last till Saturday. Saturdays are when they do their big releases. If you want beer on Saturday and they are kind of normal releases you should be able to get better till around noon. Sometimes even later. In the event that they are doing a highly anticipated collaboration you would probably want to get there sooner than later on a Saturday.
Love their Imperial IPAs and the visit to their tasting room.

Very last minute, we reach out to Other Half to book their event space. Matthew and his whole staff were amazing in helping us have the perfect space we needed. For an event, or just going for a drink, Other Half is the perfect place!
My favorite brewery. Their desert stouts!!

There are always a variety of IPAs and other delicious beers here. Highly recommended for those who like it fruity, the THANK YOU for JUICING! A small selection of current draft beers is attached in the photo. Funny interior with a direct view of the bottling plant
IPAs paradise 🍻💫

Super casual brewery! The industrial canning factory sets a great atmosphere. There is plenty of seating throughout. You can tell it’s both a local watering hole as well as a destination for beer enthusiasts. They have an extensive tap menu and have excellent and informative staff. We saw people brining food from outside restaurants to enjoy with the beers which seems like a great way to spend an evening!

Mostly, the things you look forward to disappoint you. The best of us learn that the looking is where the joy lies. I knew this could not be as good as people say…it was better. The glorious arrival in the sky over Brooklyn. Breakfast in a local deli and a walk around the post-industrial landscape waiting until 10am when it opens. I had one beer that was very good and the remaining 7 were better. Friendly service both to locals and beer tourists. Free stickers. Football. In the spirit of Michelin, worth a flight.
Great beers and lovely staff.
Non-descript location.  Don’t blink or you’ll miss it.  Fantastic beers, as always!  Great space!!!

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText:
Gotta love the Killsboro island vibes. Everything tastes better out of a mason jar and this place has the pours that tops the scores.

Great staff, satisfying duck tacos. Island Vibes baby.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Very good quality beers. Liked the NE style ones I tried there - nice and juicy.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Some of the best craft beer in NYC in my opinion. I’ve spent a lot of time sampling and traveling breweries and the owner Sean has a good thing here. They have a great selection of tapped and can beer and they hardly ever disappoint

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Island Vibes is the best IPA on the island. I come from Colorado with a lot more brewery options but this place is beyond solid. Tasty beers and EXCEPTIONAL BBQ, with even better service. We will be back!

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: I heard they have the best fried chicken and waffles in the city...i doubted that claim, but I was wrong - 20 years in the city and this is the BEST chicken and waffles.  Lots of beer diversity and they are all great!  Worth the trip over to the big island!

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Solid neighborhood brewery, only a few blocks away. Drop in here for a drink and bite to eat after a bike ride along the boardwalk! I love their IPAs (island vibes) and Parmesan garlic fries! Skip the wings. Overdone in my opinion.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: A hidden gem in Staten Island. Huge variety of craft beers, good food and very friendly staff.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Better beer than flagship easy

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: I have been coming here since they started their own brewery the food and home brewed beer is phenomenal and delicious.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Excellent brewery with small but accommodating space in the North Shore.  I had a few of the lagers and they were very well crafted.  Staff was attentive and helpful.  Would gladly stop by again.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Good craft beer and tasty burgers. Big place and nice service

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: The brisket is so tender that it melts in your mouth. My friend had the shrimp po boy and he said that was on point and something he will order again. The jalapeno cornbreads are delicious. Good job on the collard greens.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: I had 2 of their stouts and they were fantastic,  good job.

reviewText:
Food and Staff were friendly but I can never catch this place when their open.
Want to go back one day to get a more accurate assessment. When I did go the staff gave me sample beer and I just had appetizers my friends bought.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: This place is great. The food is delicious and their drinks are amazing. Reasonable prices. Definitely recommend

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText:
This place is a breath of fresh air for Staten Island. You can feel the culture and love for what they do. They have style. And most importantly, the beers are good and they always have new ones coming.

They’re on their way towards big things over there.

If you’re passing through or need to have lunch before jumping back on the ferry, I highly recommend my friends at Killsboro.

I’ve done some artwork for them to so be sure to check it out if you’re stopping by! 👨‍🎨

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Great beer!

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Good foods and good drinks. I recommend.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Staff is always super knowledgeable about the available selections, and the manager is just fantastic all around. Killsboro got me thru quarantine.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Amazing food and drinks and the staff are quick and friendly.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Good delicious, atmosphere gorgeous. Even eating outdoor dining was fanatic. Enjoyed my time there.

reviewText: consistently great food and my favorite place for sours. and the nicest people! such a gem.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301

reviewText:
Beer is not good. They do alot of trendy styles but the quality just isn't there. I would love to support them as they are local but I just doesn't do it for me.

Food is good but I'm in it for the brews.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Veggie burger amazing garlic fries on point

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Beers were pretty great. I got a flight of a few different IPAs and a cream ale, that tasted a little watery to me. But, they have some nice food and pretty bangin BBQ, so it’s definitely a good place to kill an afternoon.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Kamal is awesome!!! We had some great flights, including excellent sours. The BBQ is delicious, the atmosphere is delightful, and the craft beer is on point. Take the (free) Staten Island Ferry and a ten minute walk. You won't regret it.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText:
5 stars for their Beers: AMAZING! I love their sours and what they come up with throughout the seasons.
0 stars for their Food: abysmal...pulled pork Mac and cheese needed cheese. It was just meat and elbow noodles and also had no flavor.
$20 nachos looked incredible but tasted like nothing. I’ve never had a jalapeño that literally tasted like nothing. Not pickled. Not hot or spicy. Nothing. The black olives had to of been soaking in water. You couldn’t taste any brine they should be sitting in too tasted like nothing. The pulled pork was tender but soooo bland. There was hardly any cheese and what cheese we did find was buried at the bottom, unmelted. We had to doctor them up with a bottle of BBQ sauce and A LOT what tasted like low sodium salt...the salt needed salt. Basically it all tasted like it got rinsed under water before coming out to us. I hope it was just a really off night for them and not their norm.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301

reviewText: One of the best craft breweries in NY. Loved them since 2016. This is the OG location and has the most authentic, chill vibes.

Visiting from Australia, this was a top 3 brewery I wanted to visit in the US for the quality of their hazys. Arrived with 45 minutes until close, and the lovely blonde girl behind the bar looked after me with solid advice on what to try, tasters and staying open past close so the few left could finish their drinks. Photo of the Double Nelson daydream which was juicy and had an amazing mouthfeel with minimum sweetness from the lactose.
Fantastic beer selection, great ambiance

Finally - I'm here when the place is open!

Great brewery and a solid selection of tasty beer. Very solid juicy NE style beers.
Amazing NEIPA, perfect brewery to sit outsife and watch sunset over domino park. My fav beer was GreenCity, must try.
We visited twice while on holiday and was fabulous!Can't get fresher beer than this 👌🏻
What an absolutely fantastic place to go to get a beer. Wonderful staff and the beer is world class

Well well well

We all like it so much
Genuinely had the best beer of my life here. I buy there cans sometimes but it’s way better on tap right where it’s made
Nice brewery to drink a fresh beer.

Best craft beer and brewpub in NYC/Brooklyn, period!
🍻

Very very good beers! I strongly recommend that you stop by if you don't know it.
A very nice surprise during our vacation in NYC 😊🍻
My favorite beer in Brooklyn. Strong IPA presence in particular. During the warmer months the garage doors are open and they let the fresh air in and it's delightful.

placeAddress: 62 Van Duzer St, Staten Island, NY 10301
reviewText: Great beer, great neighborhood spot. My fav brew is Polychrome. Frequently get a growler refilled. Food is great also. My wife and I have eaten here (aka Crafthouse?) a few times. Good vibe, good staff.  Strongly recommended.

reviewText: Just got my Growler filled at Kills Boro. Well at least I thought it was full. I just paid  $24 for a 3/4 full growler. It took a while to fill. The tap must have been slow that ok with me. So the guy must have just given up when he figured he filled it enough. What's the rush? Where are you going? I'm the one waiting. Not cool.I Will not be going back.

reviewText:
I wish I could give this Starbucks zero stars. As a recurring customer who studies here often and orders coffee every day, I expected a welcoming environment, but my experience was appalling. I came in to study, fully intending to order coffee after settling in, only to be told within 10 minutes that I had to leave because I hadn’t ordered yet. Policies are one thing, but the way I was treated was unacceptable.

The owner’s attitude was shockingly rude, condescending, and dismissive. Despite being a loyal customer, I was made to feel like a burden and a criminal for simply taking a moment before placing my order. To make matters worse, the owner even accused me of lying about my intentions, despite the fact that I had no idea what he was talking about. Their tone was insulting and unprofessional, showing a complete lack of respect for customers.

To the owner, I ask:

Is this how you treat loyal customers who support your business daily?

Do you truly believe that kicking someone out within minutes is good customer service?

How do you justify speaking to customers in such a rude and disrespectful manner?

Have you considered how this kind of treatment affects your business and reputation?

If you enjoy being mistreated, by all means, visit this Starbucks. But if you value basic human decency and respect, take your business elsewhere. It’s a shame that a place I once visited daily has shown such disregard for its patrons. Absolutely disgraceful service, and I will not be returning.

EDIT: It’s clear from this lack of genuine empathy that the owner doesn’t actually care about the disrespectful experience I had. This generic response only reinforces the lack of accountability and concern.

reviewText: The staff here are rude, disrespectful and racist. One of the baristas was so drunk that she couldn’t make my order properly and I found hair in my drink

This place is decent and open late which is great if you need an after event meal. The iced matcha is so good and the polenta fries are excellent. Unfortunately there was a fresh, unsmeared lipstick print on my tea cup which is very concerning in terms of cleanliness and quality control. So check your dishes.
Good go enjoy

Chicken and waffles delicious with a maple syrup that had the right amount of heat. Fish tacos with jalepeno aioli sauce was great. Finished with an amazing blueberry sauce and bread pudding. Left stuffed and happy.

Very tasty food generally, great service. Just wished they didn't cross contaminate fried items with shellfish (dangerous for allergies). Also, got a steak and eggs breakfast on one recent visit and steak tasted fishy (2 others agreed) so that was strange. That said, the sweet breakfast items are great including the pancakes. Mac attack (3 small mac and cheese bowls) is great, although on an off day some of the bowls may be bland. Meat loaf is 5/5 at dinner.

Over the past years, we only experienced brunch, which is amazing. However, this time, we wanted to try dinner, and we weren't disappointed. The level and service, quality of food, and atmosphere were perfect for a slightly mature crowd.
Fun and lively Friday night atmosphere! Extensive menu, delicious drinks, and great service. Will definitely be back!

I come here all the time. Great food and service. The staff is amazing!!  The host Nick was very welcoming and had such great energy.  My friend and I sat at the bar after brunch, and the bartenders were extremely friendly! Love the food and staff here.  💯recommended

WOW. We already can’t wait to come back here! Nick and Atrice gave us 5⭐️ service. The food was also incredible! The truffle egg and fried chicken and waffles were perfect. I got the green juice which was also great! We’ll definitely go back- in a matter of days so we can try more of the menu and see the kind staff! 😊

Nicholas and Angel was AMAZING! The best service I’ve ever experienced in a restaurant! They were so hospitable and very enthusiastic! I couldn’t have enjoyed my brunch anywhere else! Amazing Peach Bellini & amazing bartender!!!!!

This place is such a good spot all around - we go here every week and the menu is so expansive we never run out of delicious options (highly recommend the burger, meatloaf, ginger salmon, and bread pudding). Also, the staff are super friendly (Christian is the best!) and efficient. If you want, you can be in and out in an hour, but can also be more leisurely. Cocktails are extra special - they have delicious old fashioneds and are one of few places with tasty mocktails for the sober curious :) we love this place because they don’t really cram you in with other tables - they take care to give you space and make the vibes upbeat but relaxed. Can’t recommend Cafeteria enough!

Been coming here for years and the specials I had last week were so good! My server Nick R. Was spectacular, he took such good care of me and kept me laughing the whole time. I was on a solo date and the New York stripe+bone marrow butter and the truffle mash was to die for. As always, you also can’t go wrong with the caipirinha at Cafeteria. The house music was bumping as well (great ambiance) I will certainly be back soon.

This is how you do upscale traditional American cuisine!
Went to celebrate husband’s birthday, what an amazing time we had that night 😊
Lovely service, even better food. If you are not familiar with usual dining scene of NYC, you might find it loud. But other than that, hats off.
Our favorite go to in the neighborhood! Nicholas is the absolutely nicest and most friendly Manager and always very accommodating to our family!

So my girlfriend and I were here at the Javits center for a tradeshow and we decided to pop in here and this was the first time I ever had chicken and waffles and ever since this experience I’ve been hooked now I travel around the world and I always order a chicken 🍗 and waffles 🧇 whenever there’s a restaurant that’s available to sell it!

The hot sauce and the sweet sauce went so perfectly well with the chicken 🍗 the chicken 🍗 was extremely crunchy but soft and juicy on the inside the waffles were not dry they were just perfect !

My girlfriend ordered eggs 🍳 Benny with salad 🥗 and she also really enjoyed her food it was a very very good experience the service was great the food quality was amazing and the atmosphere I absolutely loved !! 🥰 😘😘

Shared a delicious meal in a lovely, lively atmosphere. I shared the beet salad and had the ginger salmon one of my favorite dishes!
The hot tody was yummy and served quite hot so I had to wait a bit to sip it. Carmine Soprano the manager was very attentive and friendly and our waitress remembered us from previous. I sits and we got our favorite table.

BEWARE!!!! It was late and much of everything else was closed so my friend and I decided to eat here. The server we had was great he was informative and had personality. The appetizer was a mushroom soup and it was good but when the main course came it was not at all to my liking I decided on the ravioli and a side of the veggie patty. The ravioli was not good in my opinion and the veggie Pattie was okay, I took two bites from the plate and when I informed them that I didn’t like it I was told the manager would allow me to pick something else but that because the kitchen didn’t make a mistake I wouldn’t be able to take it off the bill completely. My friend had the chicken and waffles and wasn’t impressed and left most of the chicken and only really ate the waffle so I was skeptical and decided that I didn’t want to take anything and neither did he. We paid and left. I’ve never heard of such a policy but none the less BEWARE!!!
Carmen Soprano the manager makes Cafeteria feel like home! Everything is great here! The food, the vibe and the service!
Good Beer.   Classic beer
This is THE brewery you can't miss. Tasty beers, good vibes, friendly staff. Kind of a perfect place where you can enjoy the beers.
They lost my credit card

Amazing beer along with very friendly service. Was running late getting here and got in right around last call but wasn't rushed at all. Hope to come back again soon.

The spinach IPA 👌

Ok place. Generous tap list with several spectacular IPAs (the brewery's flagship). Flights available. No food. They also create several excellent pastry stouts that are seasonal (fall-winter). So if you want to try them (or buy them) it's best to go during those periods.
Best place in nyc

I visited their tap room, and enjoyed every last bit of their beers.  Hard to find a bad one from Other Half.  The place might be harder to find.  It is a grey metal door with a small "Other Half" sticker on it.  The tap room is also pretty tiny (and well decorated), so should come closer to the opening time.  Bartenders are very friendly.

Edit (Years Later): crazy how this place has grown and changed. The beers and quality still top notch though

Made the trip to the OG brewery while visiting from Australia. Well worth the trip - tried 9 different beers and all were excellent. IPAs for days. Staff were super friendly and welcoming too. Recommend.
Legit craft brews. Good vibes and music as well!

Impressive selection of beers. One standout was the 3rd Anniversary Stout which had an incredible thick consistency and a chocolatey aroma. The brewery were fine with us bringing in our own pizza to snack on with their drinks. Perfect rainy day activity.
Favorite brewery in NYC for sure. Fantastic space, even better beer, and if you go on a week night it's generally very chill.
Amazing beer!
Amazing atmosphere, very busy! Only had one beertender working and he was killing it. Extremely friendly, I'd go back just for him! The beer was fantastic!!

Second time to Cafeteria and it continues to impress! Tasty mac (of course) and tried the rock shrimp, which was a delight. However, the best part has been the cocktails and banter with Carl & Jesus at the bar. 👍👍
Alex is an amazing waitress. The food is great as well. I always have a special experience whenever I visit Cafeteria NYC.

Have had the server Nick 3 times & have had an amazing 10/10 experience each time. Been in Manhattan for the past 11+ years & this is my new fav spot bc of the consistently amazing service, incredible food (filet was amazing, chicken caesar salad was great), and fun vibe!
This place was really nice. Great food and even better desserts. The staff was friendly and cordial.

I had a wonderful experience. Great food and atmosphere.

Our server Tereza was especially amazing. Knowledgeable and down to earth - super helpful with recommendations. She ensured we never even have to think about needing something! Shrimp appetizer was so good! Short ribs were tasty and carrots yummy.

Top tier. Dessert was delicious as well as their espresso martinis.
Karl was the best bartender ever. Funny and very helpful. We will come back next sunday

Had the chicken and waffle special along with the French onion soup that was recommended to us. It was very delicious! Nick R was an amazing server, loved his personality! Good way to end my last night in NYC ☺️

Nice looking place. Fried chicken waffles, huge portion, but meat as a little dry. Note, sparkling water is $10 a bottle and they don’t come and pour the refills for you. 20% suggested tip is the lowest they start with.

I’ve never walked into Cafeteria, but I’ve ordered via DoorDash over a dozen times. For the most part, I’ve really enjoyed the food, but the times there have been issues, they’ve been big ones. Case in point, I ordered the baby gem salad today. There was not a single leaf of baby gem lettuce in the salad. Not one. It didn’t resemble the picture which features full leaves of baby gem lettuce. Frankly, it looked like  salad mix. It would have been annoying had the lettuce at least been nice romaine, but less than half was romaine. Most of it was an assortment of bitter lettuces like kale. If I’m ordered a sweet, subtle lettuce like baby gem, do not send me a salad mix consisting of bitter, unappetizing lettuces.
Jordan was the best!!!!! Excellent customer service. Would definitely come back.
Jordan is the best!!! He is amazing!!! Food is perfect!!

Grabbed brunch for the first time here today and had the best service I’ve had in the city in a while!! From the moment I came in with my group the hostess was super friendly. Our server was incredible too, very fun and attentive, he made the experience so nice for my friends and I and made helpful suggestions during the ordering process. Food was great and drinks were great too. Get the lemon ricotta pancakes and the mandarin spritz! Will definitely be back for brunch! Thank you!

We had an amazing experience here! The atmosphere had such good vibes, Nicholas was absolutely amazing, we had to have the waiter come back multiple times because there were so many good options on the menu that we couldn’t make up our minds! He was so patient and kind, and the food was AMAZING. This place is so beautiful and even though we sat outside on one of the coldest days in NY, it was still warm and cozy, bonus points for the cute blankets they left for us!
The ravioli was delish!!! The salmon not pictured was cooked perfectly.

I would have posted pictures, but the food was so good it was gone before I even had a chance to! Would definitely recommend for any brunch events!

reviewText:
After a lengthy renovation reopening their customer service and quality has  significant declined. 3 attempts to order my ice coffee correctly have failed. Each time I bring the error to the attention of the supervisor on duty I’m told I can come I could come back for a replacement. I don’t not have time to come back and even worse; I  dumped  my ice coffee received and was told need to wait until the next day for a replacement only to find
It’s also has been made incorrectly for a third time. Starbuck corporate needs to reevaluate who’s making these drinks. They are not if the true Starbucks exact customer requests and they are just mixing whatever in a cup to keep the lines moving. Unbelievable! Might be time to go back to Dunkin Donuts and give them the business. They never get it wrong. And it’s half the price . I’m very disappointed and disgusted by the Treatment, service , and quality of this Starbucks and the one on 5801 Amboy and Seguine Ave. Starbucks is dropping the ball and customer satisfaction will continue to drop until the stores get shut down, unless something is done and Cusotmer are compensated for their loss and time . Aughhh 3 days consecutively days now with out my ice coffee, since I need to dump the poorly made expensive cups of coffee. Tomorrow I’ll go to DunkinDonuts for coffee. It’s right around block too. Everyone should try going back to DD too. Save your Money and  help DD regain its worthy market share. Good by SB rudeness,  poor quality and disappointing service. Lastly, Starbucks is run on a very tight budget and noticed that all  stores  are now lacking compensation card to try and even makeup or all challenges and valuable time lost and frustration, and the self service condiments stations they used to offer , where you could add your own milks, sweeteners , and spice powders (vanilla, sweet nutmeg,  cinnamon, coca)toppings. Keeps going  downhill, get prices remain the same or have increased, for lessor everything. Do you agree?
