reviewText:
Love this place. Never dissapoint
Amazing food. Great service.
Have been coming here over 15 years.
Always a great meal to be had. Classic Chelsea fare from when Chelsea was still gay and cool.

The food was an exciting array of palate experience. The drinks were so innovative. I had the "sweet heat" which came with a giant habanero pepper as a garnish. It was smoky and spicy and tangy and just delish. It was a good time.

The venue is cramped and seating uncomfortable.  I enjoyed the fish and chips and it does compete with what I’ve had in London except the serving was small.    The cocktails are well prepared by a mixologist.  However, the alcohol content was disappointing.  I asked the waiter to have more added, instead he suggested a shot, thereby up charging me $16.   That was not cool.

Jordan, great waiter and attentive.

The manager, as well very attentive and always checking in.
nick rocz was our lovely server. every thing was delicious served on time and we were oh so taken care of. love!

Why would a place serve tasteless or generic condiments for its burgers. It just  make sense. The meatballs were good as an appetizer. The fries are pretty good.

The service here isn’t consistent. Our waiter from Ohio was very good and personable. His support staff needs a tad more training. Since we were still eating the appetizer, he sat one plate on a different table next to us. Is timing and planning his fault or the management.

The atmosphere was semi festive for the holidays.
Great comfort eats and cocktails.

Please order the muscles, literally could’ve drank the soup/sauce it came in. Just wow! There’s a lot of tourist spots in the area with mid food but this place stands out for sure. The picture btw is after we demolished everything we ordered.
Wonderful food, great service, and very kind people!
Lovely spot for brunch, food is good but sometimes limited options. The ravioli was unbearably salty but the staff apologized and offered us some free desert. The hot chocolate was so delicious.
Had a Saturday brunch with my girlfriends. Good food, good service good location. It was hard to choose what to eat because all the options look really good.

I came here on a recommendation from a long time New Yorker and all I can say is wow! The food is amazing but the service is even better -- Nick Rocz took our good experience to great! Thank you Nick and Cafeteria!

placeAddress: 4916 Arthur Kill Rd, Staten Island, NY 10309
placeName: Beans and Leaves Coffee and Tea Cafe
reviewText:
Not the best place for working. I was looking for a quiet cafe to drink coffee and work on my laptop, and I wouldn't recommend this spot. The seating isn't ideal and the more you sit there, the more you notice it. The chairs were too low and the table was too high. I'm shorter than average, but I'm not tiny by any means. These tables made me feel minature. The table was close to my shoulder height, and when I tried to use my laptop, my elbows couldn't rest on the table.

Also, it isn't very clear that you can ONLY order at the counter. When I entered, I was sat at a table and handed a menu. The other guests and I were confused about if there was wait service. It wasn't made clear that there is not, and everyone needs to order at the counter.

I had a waffle with butter and syrup, and it was serviceable. Beans & Leaves Cafe is definitely more of a brunch spot. It's a cute location with a cozy ambiance, but for the reasons I mentioned before, it needs improvements before I would consider coming back.

reviewText: I didn't even get into the front door. There is a dress code, for what reason? I don't know. But I wasn't allowed in because I was wearing a hat. Stylish it may be...but no hats are allowed in a restaurant called " The Cafeteria" You gotta be in the upper echelon to eat here.
Came for brunch with two young children. Treated us  like royalty. The food was great, the decor was great. The service impeccable.

Sourly disappointed by my entire experience here. I grew up going here with family, especially on thanksgiving. My last experience here was awful. I brought my cousin, who is trans, here to celebrate the holidays for thanksgiving this year. The amount of constant misgendering and disrespect was foul. That alone was deserving of the 1 star, but it certainly didn’t help that the food quality has noticeably gone down, and the portions were so small for the price. Will never step foot in here again. Another New York City gem gone to dust. Do better.
Service was amazing. Food was great. 10/10

Came here for my friends “21” birthday

Omg!! What a fun time!!
Nick our server made the whole night like a standup!! So funny

He knew the whole menu and knew what to offer us. Give us a round of drinks at the end of night!

Come on Friday and see him so effin fun!!!
Incredible pork chop, great service!

This place is so cozy, great energy, great music, great food, and most importantly great service! Alex B. was our host this evening, and she took exceptionally good care of us. Very attentive, anticipated our needs, and notably kept up the fantastic service with other surrounding tables in her section. The portions here are great and totally worth every penny. We ordered the Chicken Bao buns, Mussels (white cream sauce and aioli coated toast - to die for), and we both opted for the meatloaf. Solid choices on all fronts. Also enjoyed some delicious old fashioned’s throughout our experience. Can’t wait to return to try some other menu options! Check this place out if you are in the Chelsea area, or NYC in general for that matter.

Tereza was a blessing. She was friendly, very attentive, and knowledgeable about the menu. She helped out with our food options, and gave great drink options as well. Loom forward to our next time here.

Cafeteria is iconic. This used to be the spot you go to after the clubs. Mac and cheese sampler is great, steak is great, mussels are great, lamb burger is great, cocktails are great (and under $18 each! a steal in this economy, imo) The vibe is always sexy, but casual. You can go have a nice date, but also hang with friends and maybe make new ones as well. The outdoor dining is heated and cute and decorated as well. I would say that the most appealing thing about this place is that it is tried and true and reliable. If all else fails, Cafeteria is there for you.

When I visit my son in NYC, Cafeteria is the first restaurant we go to for dinner. Great atmosphere, service, and an eclectic menu that accommodates most dietary needs - it's a guaranteed great start to our visit together!
Nick R.  was amazing , his recommendations were on point . Service was top notch , hospitality at its core

As a regular guest one of the things I love about Cafeteria is that the service is always great, but Nick this evening was exceptional. It is great to see him training other waiters to continue the Cafeteria tradition of warm, welcoming, attentive charming and fun service.

Always loved this place, BUT the man at the front desk tonight who worked the 11:39 timerange was disgustingly rude. At an establishment like this greeters should be advised to treat people with respect. You can get your point across without being a nasty person. Also if you close at 12am then adjust hours to 11pm so people arent wasting their time.
Good brunch! We ate at the bar since it was quite busy. But were able to sit right away. The chicken and waffles were really tasty! The cheesy grits were so yummy.
Came here for lunch  with my friend Les and food was delicious and service and ambiance was amazing, Brandon the Manger was great and helpful.

reviewText:

Local owned, local run.  Great people, great service, great products.

Once you experience, you'll pass by ⭐$s every time.

Experience was mediocre, staff seemed either tired and ready to go home or just had poor customer service skills. My wife and I opted for the Baked Apple and Cheesecake flavors.

The ingredients used were not fresh, our strawberries and apples tasted stale. The thin slice of cheesecake was bland and the amount of ice cream given for the outrageous over charge is ridiculous. Overall for $37, I would definitely spend it else where next time around.
Definitely one of the best crepes I've tried in the city of NYC, my forever favorite is the New Yorker with Nutella!

Staff is much nicer than the west 4th staff. Hours are amazing with delectable crepes! 3am binge crepe after drinks! We had tres leche , strawberry cheesecake w dulcet de leche! Doesn't get better than that!
Not worth the money, crepe was very dry, never again.
Strawberries are either not ripe or rotten - if your charging $15 for a crepe the strawberries should at least be half way decent. Would not recommend
Good crêpes
THE BEST
The crepes here are delicious!
Terrible service. They wanted to charge extra for the ice cream and whip cream I never heard of this. Cold strawberry and banana terrible. No napkins or fork. Had to ask for that.
Awesome as always! Love it
$11 dollars for crepe that’s finished in 3 bites
We had the spinach crepe and the fruit crepe with milk chocolate—everything was super tasty. We especially loved their baked apples.
Thank you very much. I think very Good company polite. Good staff quickly help to open an account quick Answer to all questions I think we will work together for a long time.
Been going here since 2019 the OG spot if you know you know.
Best hot chocolate in NYC

This is the cutest churro shop with delicious churros. Don’t let the plastic sample foods on the counter fool you. The plain churros with a sauce are divine and definitely a must-do in NYC! Not to be missed!
Absolutely delicious. No frills or gimmicks, just amazing churros and ice cream. Loved it.
So yummy

The kind of place that makes you come back every time you're in town. Friendly staff and cozy atmosphere. Especially enjoyable churros and espresso experience while seated outside during spring or autumn.

Did you just hear that? That's the sound of your dessert dreams calling in New York City. 🤤 La Churreria is serving up golden, crispy churros that are about to redefine your sweet tooth. Seriously, these aren't just churros, they're a moment. Imagine: warm, crunchy perfection dipped in decadent chocolate, dulce de leche, or whatever your heart desires. Are you drooling yet? 😉

Fascinating hideaway in Soho, it is worth entering and trying their tasty churros, a small and very cozy place, totally romantic and eclectic. Churros are tasty and inexpensive, nothing better than making a stop to recharge your batteries. Everything there is positive, excellent service, structural warmth and the most delicious churros.
Love this place, will be back again (and again)!!! Gonna go back tomorrow actually lol 😆
We LOVE La Churreria!! Each trip to NYC (from California) requires a mandatory trip here! YUM!!!
The churros were delicious. I got churros with ice cream. The only thing is that the space is very small and crowded. I would get take out instead.

I love this place, super cozy, it is always decorated according to the season and any important celebration, their churros are not a delight, now they have many different types of churros, the chicolTe is very good, they have a very delicious lentil soup. A very reasonable price, when you go to Soho don't forget to try these delicious churros.
super cute and awesome and yum
Small coffee shop but has amazing churros!! I loved the dulche de leche filled one, it was crunchy and perfectly filled. Their hot chocolate is also as good. The size of the drinks are a bit small
20-Oct
I totally love this place.  I enjoy myself every time I go. I've never had a bad experience. ❤️

Jenna was an amazing server! The food was so delicious and well prepared (I had the salmon tar tar and lamb burger per her recommendation.) Cocktails were top notch as well. The ambiance was cozy but felt very chic and trendy at the same time. I had an overall fantastic experience. Can’t wait to come back to try more of the menu and experience excellent service from the whole team at Cafeteria. 10/10 no notes

My parents and I went here for the first time as per a nice woman’s recommendation who overheard us talking about where to eat on the street lol. Absolutely loved the atmosphere, food and service! Our waiter, Nick (also dressed as beetle juice for the night) couldn’t have made it more of a welcoming dining experience!! Such a fun, genuine person through and through, and yes we loved the food but I think we’d go back solely to see him again. Could not recommend this place more 10/10. I personally got the lamb burger and would totally recommend!
The fries are bad, the milkshake is nothing like it, the hamburger is good, very expensive for the food they sell so much.
My favorite spot in the city.  Great atmosphere and food.
Pancakes, French toast, Any cocktail and please try any mac&chesse! AMAZING!

We had a great time celebrating a friend's birthday.
It was a nice chill vibe and the music had everyone moving in their seats.
Our server Nick R made our night even better.
Definitely recommending this place and Nick to other people.
I’d just like to say when you go request Nick R! He is literally the best. He is so attentive, funny and charismatic. He made the experience 100x’s better than it already was!
Love the waiters! Absolutely amazing food even though it can get a bit crowded. You don’t feel rushed and they take care of you!
I finally found a meatloaf I genuinely enjoy, and want again, plus the service was extremely top tier
The service was great and I will come back and will recommend this place. I’m telling you they have great service and Brandon made sure we were satisfy with his services
A super friendly staff delivered a yummy brunch for my wife and I.  Highly recommend.

Popped in here after dinner last night for a night cap and despite it being so late, the staff was SO accommodating and lovely. Our server Nick was delightful and full of energy and also the negronis were 10/10!!
Great food

A little setting in the heart of New York that recalls the Chocolatería San Ginés in Madrid and serves churros that have nothing to envy of it! I went there with a friend to try their ice cream churros caramel sandwich and it was truly delicious! I would be happy to come back and try their other creations like the one with Catalan cream or the monthly ephemerals 🫶short little crush, and many people recommended the hot chocolate so to try it next time.

Too cute not stop in , and to go for a yummy treat . Churro bites with side of hot chocolate dipping sauce , and stuffed dulce leche churro are definitely recommended. Will return  for a warming treat .
Best churros you'll ever have in NYC!

If you are ever in Lower Manhattan and in need of some sweet desserts, you should check out this snug little spot hidden on Mulberry Street! This hidden gem offers teas and beverages, but is known for their churros! Feel free to sit down and dine in, or take out if you're in a rush. If you do plan on dining in, please get there early, as there are limited seating!

I recommend getting the mini stuffed churro box. Great to share with a friend or family member, or to enjoy for yourself. Each can be devoured in a bite or two, with several flavors to choose from.

The churro picnic box is another fabulous choice. The hot chocolate was more dark than sweet, which was perfect as the churros had sugar on them. The strawberry was strong, but was a good counter to the dark hot chocolate sauce. The dulce de leche was my favorite sauce, although it was solid and made it difficult to scoop with the churro.

Definitely check out their monthly specials! I plan on returning to try next month's special, as well as, all the months that follows!

I came across this spot on Instagram and decided to give it a try since everything looked delicious—and it did not disappoint! The place is small but very cute and cozy, with a warm atmosphere. Service was quick and welcoming. They offer a variety of churros, and I have to say, these are the best we’ve ever had! The churros are lightly sweet, perfectly crunchy, and not overly coated in cinnamon sugar like most places.
We ordered the Autumn Lollipop, the Apple Churro Sundae, and the Churro Crème Brûlée—each one was incredible. We also tried their lentil soup (supposedly a fan favorite) and one cheese empanada, which was perfectly crispy and filled with gooey cheese.
This place is a gem, and I’d recommend it!
Was so good great cozy spot friendly environment 😊
Churro ice cream sandwich, salted caramel. The churro was warm and delicious. The service was great. No wait on a Friday evening.

This place is fantastic for desserts, lattes, and sweets. The churros were amazing, and the crème brûlée was to die for—soft, warm, crunchy, and simply delicious. Don't expect a full dinner; this spot is more of a breakfast or snack bar. The Halloween decorations are cute, and the staff is lovely.

Be patient if there's a line, trust me, it's worth it! The staff is super friendly and efficient and try to get you through the line quickly but everything is fresh so waiting a little for your order is expected.
We ordered the plain churro bites with a side of the dulce de leche sauce and the Churro Creme Brulee. Let me tell you, these churros are perfection. I've been all over Mexico, Spain, Portugal and have had many churros, these are not greasy, they are perfectly crispy and that creme brulee topping is just so good. Definitely worth the wait. The rest of their menu looks good and I'll definitely come back to try their food next time.

A nice specialized dessert place primarily for crepes. They also offer drinks like bubble tea and even savory crepe options! But the sweet crepes are rightfully the main attraction, with combinations inspired directly by many famous sweets like Kinder, Rocher Ferrero, and smores.
The shop looks small but they have a decent amount of seating and the menus are all pretty large, though some writing can be a bit difficult to see. The staff make the crepes behind the glass case so you can watch. It's best if you order ahead, I think, since it takes about 10 minutes to make two crepes when it wasn't crowded.
The crepes are decently supple and can hold up to a fork and knife while retaining most of the filling or what sauce doesn't squeeze out.
Their schedule can be a little funny since they close on Mondays, but I do recommend coming here to satisfy a sweet craving.

I stopped by Creperie NYC after dinner down the street, and as always, they did a phenomenal job! I’ve been coming here for years, and their crepes never disappoint. This time, I went with their original famous crepe—strawberries, bananas, Nutella—with my personal twist: adding white chocolate for balance and a scoop of ice cream. It was perfection!

We also tried the viral Dubai chocolate strawberries, which were layered with bits of knuffa pistachio cream and Nutella. Every bite was a perfect blend of flavors, and it’s clear they put a lot of thought into how it’s made.

Despite how busy they were, the service was great—quick and efficient. Seating is limited, but enjoying the warm crepes outside added to the experience. I’m also happy to see they now take credit cards (it used to be cash-only). It’s nice to know that even with small changes, their quality remains top-notch.

Highly recommend this spot if you’re in the area!
One of the best crepes in lower east side a must try!

The combination of fresh fruit with Nutella and ice cream was indulgent without being overly heavy—a perfect balance of flavors.

I recently visited Dhaba with a friend who came all the way from Florida, and it was an unforgettable dining experience! The restaurant has a great vibe, and the food was absolutely delicious.

We ordered the Chicken Tahadi Kabab as a starter, and it was incredibly unique and flavorful—A must-try! For the main course, we had the Goat Biryani, Garlic Naan, and Lamb Rogan Josh. The biryani was aromatic and perfectly spiced, the naan was soft and buttery, and the lamb curry was rich and tender, absolutely divine!

The service was prompt, and the staff was friendly and attentive. I’ve been here before based on reviews, and this time, bringing my friend here was just as satisfying. If you’re in New York and craving authentic Indian cuisine, Dhaba is the place to go!

A special shoutout to the chef for crafting such amazing dishes. Each bite was a burst of flavor, and it’s clear that a lot of care and expertise goes into the food. Thank you for making our meal so memorable!

Highly recommend it for anyone looking for a great meal and a warm atmosphere. Can’t wait to come back!

One of the best Indian restaurants in New York City, in my opinion. We started with many appetizers, including Pani Puri and Lamb Seekh Kebab. All of them were perfect and authentically Indian. We were blown away by the generous portion sizes, as compared to other places in the area. We were also surprised by the service, as it was very swift. Next, we got our main courses. They included Malai Marke Butter Chicken, Dal Makhani, and Methi Mutter Malai. All of them exceeded our expectations, as they were all incredibly tasty, and all of them were very authentic. The atmosphere was dim, making it cozy and inviting. My only criticisms:
- the door brings in cold wind drafts
- the bathroom is somewhat dirty
- the tables are a little unstable
But generally, incredible restaurant and exceeded all of our standards in service, atmosphere, and food alike. 5 stars.

Aside from the over cramped seating and limited buffet options, there are worse things to experience at this restaurant. The owner and staff are always walking about staring at you when you take a second serving on the buffet table. Why hold a buffet if you don’t want people to eat more? They dismiss you by glaring, acting rude and ignoring you the entire time. My colleagues and I (group of 5) went last week for the buffet. After requesting the 2nd bread basket (4 pieces of naan in it), the staff started ignoring us point blank every time we requested more naan. The next servings of naan was brought to us by the owner himself and announces ‘looks like the baskets are piling up’ in a very aggressive tone. Again, why host a buffet if you don’t want people to eat? Amongst 5 of us we had three naans. In no way was that too many and there was no cause for the owner or staff to behave this way. Rude, arrogant and disrespectful. Absolutely the worst indian restaurant in NYC. Food was mid at best.

reviewText: WARNING: DON’T GO UNLESS YOU LIKE WASTING MONEY ON BS! First and LAST time me and my family will be going to Decker Farm! There was an admission fee to get inside, which I was aware of because it says the admission or “ticket prices” on their website, even though they didn’t have actual tickets; they just stamp your hand after you pay. So we get stamped to go inside the farm, but when we get in there was literally NOTHING as advertised for the kids to do and it was a HUGE disappointment. Both of my kids are on the spectrum for autism and were looking forward to a fun time on the farm, but instead they got nothing but disappointment. They charge you to basically go on the property, but EVERYTHING else inside cost money and their prices are far from cheap. They advertised pumpkin painting, hayride, pumpkin chucking, and more fun activities for the kids, but you have to pay for everything (except the hayride, but that was so wack that it wasn’t even worth going)! We were so unhappy with our experience there that we didn’t even do their hayride because it was pointless. I was under the impression that certain things or activities would have been included in the admission fee, but they literally charge you to walk around and it’s not right. My oldest (9 years old) told me this wasn’t fun AT ALL. I felt so bad because I really thought we would have a nice family fun day, but it just wasn’t the case at this farm. This place is definitely a money scam and something needs to be done with them! I decided it wasn’t worth it and took them elsewhere for better fun. Not to mention they’re toys they had available for the kids we can easily get at a dollar store for literally $1.25 and they try to charge $7! IT’S INSANE!!! As we were leaving I tried talking to a manager asking for a refund or even half (it was a simple cash transaction), but she said it’s a fundraiser event and they can’t give refunds on it. I double checked afterwards on their website and it says NOTHING about being a fundraising event. The place was not as advertised and I wasted my last dollars for absolutely nothing! NOT COOL!!!

reviewText: I like to grab some pastries cake and sandwich here when pass by Hylan, just want to make sure all sandwiches are fresh especially avocado turkey one, Overall love it!

I purchased my wife a large birthday cake. Once we cut into the cake, we found out that around 1/3 third of the cake wasn’t actually sponge cake but was filled with just cream. That is very deceptive.  If I order and pay for large birthday cake, you should not give me small cake with the centre filled with cream to make it appear larger. I’ve never been so disappointed. From the attached picture you can see how small the actual cake is, the white middle is just pure cream no sponge.

Edit. The email address provided in the business’s response does not work.  That’s very unprofessional.

The donut filled with cream was delicious! I also got chocolate filled croissant that was great as well (both pastries were not too sweet, which was great). Their iced latte was one of the best ones I had in a while. Will be ordering again.

I’m sorry to leave this review but it’s necessary. The OVERPRICED pastries are insane. 3 pastries for +$30 is too much, and it’s not even fresh. Staff is friendly enough to make your visit smoother but their prices are above the sky!!

Nice atmosphere and decent selections.  However, when it comes to sandwiches, the egg salad and tuna salad come only with white bread which is a mistake in the era of health-conscious folks who prefer at least whole grain, rye, whole wheat or even gluten-free options.  Yes it's a bakery, but why stop folks like me from visiting?  Why not at least have the same bread option as the chicken salad or the turkey sandwich?   Will change to 5 stars if and when the white bread is removed.  We get plenty of that with the baked goods anyway.
I love this place, it's very cozy and the pastries are delicious, sometimes my husband and I come here to sit and eat, sometimes I takes something delicious out
not bad but DONT GET THE MACAROONS

The ham and cheese baguette I ate was nice. I had it heated-up which made a difference. I washed it down with a cold bottle of diet coke, I didn't see any fountain service. Things that detracted were the unclean tables and loud ambient volume. My companion came up to the counter while I was waiting on my order and asked for a table wipe-down. I had gotten my order and walked over toward the table my companion chose. Several tables that needed a wipe down were between our furthest-from-counter table and the counter. Some had debris on them. Our table was wiped down but the other tables were not while we were there. It looks like an interesting concept but between kids  screaming or crying and the poorly maintained seating area the tasty food had an uphill battle. Still, I gave it a 4 star rating, likely too generous but I did have excellent company which clearly nudged me toward a kinder disposition on reflection. I did see plenty of pastries and cakes that looked delicious and were well presented. My visit was on a Sunday which could mean that at best I had been served by the "B-team." Still, wipe downs should be ubiquitous regardless of which shift is working. Would I return? Maybe during a weekday. That baguette WAS good. 😋
Incredible!!

I ordered a crepe cake from the store today for my mom’s birthday. I placed an order in the morning and scheduled to pick up at 5pm. The cake tastes horrible. The cake doesn’t seem to be freshly made, the texture is so hard. The crepes are not soft and creamy at all. And it costs 64$ and it’s totally not worth it! Most importantly, it ruined my mom’s bday.  Paris, I am very disappointed. I demand a full refund!

Tried Paris Baguette for the first time yesterday, just grabbing a late coffee with a friend, they had a nice selection of pastries to choose from, it’s a very calm and relaxed environment. Staff was really friendly and the food was very good overall.
Love it no

I came inside the store and ordered a medium hot latte, a cronut, and a plain croissant. The service was very nice. The establishment was orderly, clean, and had beautifully arranged display cases with an inviting layout. However, understanding how to navigate the ordering process requires a bit of familiarity. Fortunately, when there’s a steady flow of customers, it’s easy to observe those who’ve been here before—knowing to grab tongs and a plastic tray, then follow the line to place orders. There’s also a direct line for orders, making things fairly streamlined.

Upon receiving my coffee, I found it strange that despite being prompted to tip using the new computerized payment system, I still had to add my own sugar and condiments to a meticulously prepared coffee. An establishment of this level, given the price charged and the implied service fee, should be customizing drinks per customer order.

Now for the products:
•   The Cronut: This was my first-ever cronut, and sadly, it didn’t leave me wanting another one. While the texture succeeded in capturing the flakiness of a croissant, it completely missed the essence of what makes a donut enjoyable. Instead of a balanced pastry, it felt like an overly indulgent croissant filled with an overwhelming amount of buttercream, topped with sugar, and finished with even more cream. The buttercream itself was lackluster, lacking the richness and flavor expected from a dessert at this price point.
•   The Plain Croissant: The dough was rolled imperfectly, leaving a large hollow in the middle, suggesting no differentiation between how they prepare filled versus plain croissants. This shows a lack of respect for the traditional butter croissant, where layers should be evenly distributed and delicate. Additionally, the butter used had a much higher salt content, which might make sense when paired with sweet fillings, but it was far too salty for what a classic butter croissant should be.

Overall, it was an okay experience. The staff was polite, full of smiles, and the establishment itself was clean and welcoming. Hopefully, with time and attention to detail, these issues will be addressed. I may return and update this review if things improve, as I take my reviews seriously. If you don’t see an update, this is how my experience stands.

They sell nice , fancy pastry but at what price!!  ; last time I bought something from there that was a tiny heart shaped  Valentines cake that cost me $54 !!   TOO EXPENSIVE store ; stay away if you care about your wallet.

The pastries were divine—each one a little masterpiece of flavor and texture. I tried the croissant and a strawberry cake slice, and both were fresh, buttery, and simply delicious.

The staff was incredibly friendly and attentive, making sure I had everything I needed. The quality and variety of baked goods are unmatched—whether you’re craving savory or sweet, there’s something for everyone.

I can’t wait to come back and try more from their amazing menu. Paris Baguette has quickly become my go-to spot for a little taste of heaven. Highly recommend!

It is absolutely worth it to try every day to learn all the different flavorful meat and vegetable foods they have. Try to learn the names of each food. The star of the show was the puff for sure. It was fluffy, had ample amounts of cream, and packed a punch with fruity flavors! If you are not a fan of fruit flavored desserts, I would stay away as the passion fruit and guava flavors are strong. It was a wonderful treat and I would want to try the other puffs next.

The staff were quite nice, and the shop was nice, despite being pretty small.

Worth stopping by if you’re in the area.

placeAddress: 435 Richmond Hill Rd, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText:
I’m only rating Decker Farm for their fall festival, since we have not visited for any other occasion.

First thing that is wrong with this festival, You have to pay to get in. What does that get you? It gets you the privilege of paying WAY too much for disgusting, burnt Arepas, stale donuts & popcorn. You get to stand in line for 30min to ride on a 10min hayride that does a small loop. You also get to pick a pumpkin that they probably bought at Trader Joe’s for $5 and put in their field and then charge you $30 for! The only free thing other than the hayride is a little hay maze for kids under 6, and I mean little.

The traffic to get there is crazy and there’s practically no parking.

The only reason I gave 2 stars instead of 1 was because there are a few ok photo opps and the pumpkin launcher, which also cost extra, was a little fun.

Food was good, service was on point and the chef Kuldeep Singh was really a nice guy!

kudos to your team!
Good Food Good Hospitality ❤️👌
Authentic indian food.. great atmosphere.. fabulous

I found the place to be very cozy, with dim lighting and Indian music creating a pleasant atmosphere. I went with my Korean colleagues eager to try Indian food, and we all enjoyed the meal. The food was great, though the dessert could have been a bit sweeter. They provide regular naan, but garlic naan is an extra dollar each. Overall, it’s a nice spot worth visiting!
Very  nice ambiance and very good food. Chef Kuldeep Singh is amazing.
Can't recommend this place, mediocre at best.
Best Indian food in Lexington if you re visiting new York and looking Indian food dhaba is the best option amazing service and food chefs are coming to table & explain about the food it was wow

If you're looking for a review of this place to see if the food is authentic, it is not at all authentic.
The fact that they call their food "Indian cuisine" is a joke. We ordered their Dal Makhani and Aloo Matar, two very different dishes, and both the dishes had literally the same base, just the toppings were different. The saddest part is the one base they make is also flavorless and watered down.
We also ordered the Mushroom Malai Waali, and that was flavorless as well.
I am Indian, and the fact they are associating this with Indian food is a disgrace.
I was amazed at how bad the food was, and I was compelled to leave this review so that people who want to eat good food do not fall for this joke like I did.

It was really great experience at Dhaba. We had weekday buffet and liked saag paneer, daal, bhuna chicken. Kuldeep Singh was really humble and we were very happy with the service. Last but not the least Suji halwa was also great.

Best Indian food in Manhattan. If you're visiting New York for the first time this place is your first stop. I amejoyed the Dahba Goat curry and the Lemon rice. Service is outstanding. Aakanksha was amazing.

Been meaning to go to Dhaba for a fee years now but never got around to it. Well worth the wait, the food was delicious. The buffet had a good variety of veg and meat. The Naans were my favourite, had a plain and garlic naan, cant go wrong. Stand out dishes at the buffet were the chicken madras and paneer. Ended with kheer (rice pudding) had to get a second helping, it was that good. Give Dhaba a try, you won't be disappointed.
Glad I tried this place. I'm definitely coming back, there's too much to choose from.
Closed at 10:30

Lunch Buffet Review: Very good food, taste of some vegetables could be better, like Saag Paneer, and Vegetable Korma. Baigan Bharta really nice, dal was great, kheer was great. I must say worth the price. ($20/plate)

Service: Excellent, cheching with us continously.

Atmosphere: Clean, hygienic.

I would recommend this place for lunch buffet in NYC.

I ate at this restaurant while in New York for work a few months ago. To be honest this is one of the best Indian restaurants that I’ve been to in the US. The food was absolutely outstanding and the service was overall pretty good… I believe the owner came to each of the tables to see how people were doing. The biryani and vegetarian options are phenomenal. I would definitely go back if I was in New York City again
Awesome food, good options in veg and Non Veg...had very good experience.

Best Indian food I have had in USA in last 20 years.  Kuldip(main chef) personally came and made food the way we wanted it...most friendly crew.  Please do visit this place if you are in Manhattan*****
Amazing place with amazing food
Great croissant 🤤🥐 That's all I needed.
I had the apple puff and it was amazing!! The chocolate eclair was very rich but if you’re a chocolate lover you’ll enjoy
This chocolate chip cookie was dense and gooey. It wasn’t too sweet which was nice. I did find that there are better chocolate chip cookies out there though.

Absolute favorite pastry/dessert place. I love desserts that are sweet and tart and this place delivers. You MUST try the passion fruit flavor. If you want just sweet, their chocolate or cinnamon rolls are decadent. Everything they make is quality. The pastries are beautiful and will make a great impression. They are art on a plate. But even more importantly, they are absolutely delicious. The service is also excellent. This is my go-go place for every holiday (I always bring the dessert). Btw, the photo is of passion fruit pastry on Bolesławiec pottery from Poland.
Traveled just for a choux au craquelin because of the TV show Mashle, and they had an apple pie puff that was delicious. Friendly staff; will come back again.

I stopped into Petit Chou and was very impressed by their great selection of pastries. Everything looks very well made and tastes fresh. I got 3 pastries for about $20 - I think this is a bit on the high end as most were priced around $7.5 to $8. The chocolate chip cookie was about $5.

The pistachio eclair which had an amazing presentation. The cream was not overly sweet and the fresh pistachios on top balanced out the flavor.

The thick chocolate chip cookie had great texture. It was pretty sweet, but they didn’t go light on the chocolate which I love.

The croissant breakfast sandwich was the star of the show. It had egg, cheese, and bacon in a wonderfully light croissant shell. One downside is that it was very, very oily. Definitely don’t think I could finish one whole sandwich myself, so I’m glad I was sharing.

Overall a place to check out. They don’t have seating inside the shop, so I’d recommend taking the pastries to go.

I’m shocked by these good reviews, and would not be surprised if some are AI, or from lots of neighbors/friends. These pastries were UNBELIEVABLY bad. You could get better pastries at Safeway! The breading was terrible. These pastries are costly and low quality. The eclairs were the worst I’ve EVER had (frozen eclairs are even better). The passionfruit dessert was barely ok.

My friends and I were excited to stop in after dinner when we saw the positive reviews, and one bite in we were shocked (in a terrible way.)
Real France!!! Rare quality for America. Buy it with confidence! Excellent👍❤️‍🔥
The best bakery I've been to in East Village, especially the banana cream pie. I could eat that everyday.

-Double chocolate croissant: my favorite thing to get here!! It is dense, and so rich of chocolate
-Chocolate chip cookie: I heated it up for 10 sec in the microwave but it was too gooey for me. Probably could’ve been better not heated up
-Pistachio eclair: it’s okay to me

Service is always very friendly!
Would love to try their cinnamon roll one day.
Pastry was good. Breakfast sandwich didn't live up to the hype. Tasted like a kraft grilled cheese sandwich

I had a passion fruit cheesecake puff and it was exceptional. There was a tiny passion fruit cheesecake on top, and the puff was filled to the brim not only with cheesecake cream, but this amazingly tangy, concentrated passion fruit curd.
The bacon egg and cheese with the side of chipotle sauce hmmm!
The food is delicious: I got an Éclair and a Quiche.
Definitely, I will come back for it. It’s one of the most delicious pastry.

The bread at this Paris Baguette is more expensive than in Jersey which makes sense. The problem is… the bread seems to always be a bit burnt compared to others. Especially the red bean rice donut. It’s one of my favorites but the one at this located is HARD!! Some other pastries also seem notably more cooked than it should be…
What a place !! So clean, a dessert paradise! Everything looks absolutely delicious!! I want to try everything !! I'll be back

Definitely overpriced specially for the size of any dessert you get it's ridiculous iced coffee was very watery definitely not worth the price rather go to a piece of cake up the block any day you're just paying for the name not worth it.... The slice of strawberry shortcake is half the size of any other bakery which is usually better tasting also.

MOLD FOUND ON CAKE!!!!
BAD SERVICE!!!
today at 8:35 I spent over $90 on the bakery items! I bought 2cakes slice to gift my family members today I kept one to myself I dropped the two ther cakes slice I got home opened my cake and I look at the first bite I SAW A DROP OF MOLD so embarrassing to tell my other family members  that there might be MOLD on theirs. YOU WOULD expect fresh cake slices in the morning. So I called THERE NUMBER and the lady that answer me I explain to her she sounds irritated LEAVES ME ON HOLD!!! and she HUNG UP ON ME!! Instead of helping the situation she wasn’t even fazed????? now I have a Mother’s Day cake how am I gonna eat that in peace knowing the other one had MOLE!!!  (I took a video of my cake slice and so I had to screen shot the photo to post on here)

I'm happy they exist.
They have a delicious selection of lattes, etc.
It rivals the Starbucks down the block - plus, come on, the bread selection is on point.
This particular location is spacious enough with a welcoming vibe.
A nice place to chill in between returning packages to the UPS store and shopping at the supermarket.
Go. It's worth it.
Impressive selection of pastries 🍰 🥐🍩 great coffee & spacious feel.

Paris Baguette is my go-to bakery for delicious pastries and treats! The moment you walk in, you're greeted by the heavenly aroma of freshly baked goods. Their selection is extensive, from fluffy croissants to decadent cakes, there's something for everyone. The quality is consistently high, and the presentation is impeccable. The staff is always friendly and helpful, making the whole experience even more enjoyable. Whether I'm grabbing a quick snack or picking up treats for a special occasion, Paris Baguette never disappoints. Highly recommend!
Pastry was stale and the peppermint latte didn’t taste like peppermint at all. Considering the price and reputation of Paris,  this was a huge letdown. Tables were also dirty.
Clean friendly atmosphere. Delicious selection of pastries and desserts.

bought bday cake,cashier didnt bother to ask if i need knife/candle so i gotta buy my own, fine, but i dunno how old the cake is, must be stored in the fridge for thousand years, fruit and cake both taste dry and bland. not going back for sure
Love this place! Pastries, cakes, bread, salad, they’re all good. So glad we have this in our town.
Why is this place called The Paris Baguette when THEY DON'T SELL BAGUETTES?
One of my all time favorite coffe and pastry shops snd I can’t believe it made it to Staten Island. You won’t ever go wrong have coffe or a pastry from here.
Absolutely wonderful!
Amazing! Especially Michelle she works so hard!!

I love Paris baguette but kind disappointed with this one . On my husband’s birthday I bought a soft-cream strawberry cake and some other pastries. Pastries were delicious and fresh but the strawberry cake ! Cream and fruits were good but the base sponge cake wasn’t that fresh can taste it was so watery !
Wow nice place
The most delicious pastries!! Friendly service, nicely organized, and fast service even when busy. I have visited a few times already and will be going back too many more! Lol
Nothing “Paris” or French about it — Chinese takeout with no cozy European cafe atmosphere. Dry pastries made with cheap bleached ingredients. Made with zero love and minimal effort.
The food was amazing and we like the All the veg item
Amazing food and really attentive and kind servers! Will definitely come back.

I had the lunch buffet here on August 23, 2024.  A couple of dishes, the mixed vegetable one (I forget the name) and the dal makhani - surprisingly - were very spicy. The mutter paneer and the aloo palak were fine. The sooji (semolina) halwa was just sad, you could see the dark parts that had been over-roasted.

Well, I didn't eat much else for the rest of the day except for some Pepto and yogurt in an attempt to subdue the heartburn that extended well into the night.
The food was good.

Super delicious food 🍛
Fabulous service 👍🏻

Very good food , the kabab with mint chutney was mind blowing, the server was very good , visited this restaurant first time and it was a good pick to be honest, visited from Canada , 5 star for food and service.
Not open

I came there Sunday evening with my family for dinner the food was astounding with great service we were seated directly by the window which I loved. We are definitely coming back again for some delicious Indian meals. If u are nearby this is a must try restaurant
Great lunch buffet friendly service.
Good food and take caring service. Equally treat to all even takeout , impressive
Average at best. Malai kofta was loaded with sugar.
Craving for real Desi food? This is the place!
Authentic Indian food taste in Manhattan, great service especially by Nishant, reasonably priced

This has happened to me twice at this restaurant. I went there with my Caucasian husband. I am Asian. When walking in, manager did not smile at me but motioned by pointing to a corner seat. My husband got the biggest grin.

We were seated all the way in the corner. When I sat facing the restaurant, no wait staff approached us for solid 10 minutes. I made eye contact with few of them. No one approached us. Then I suggested doing a social experiment and switched seats with my husband so that he can sit facing the restaurant. I kid you not, within seconds, 2 people showed up asking if we are ready to order. After that, it was all smiles and good service.

Being India born, I try really hard to forget the amount of racism we eastern featured citizens endured by fellow Indians back home. It’s been so many years. It still shakes me to the core when I see blatant racism by none other than Indians who have experienced ample amount of racism themselves. We don’t need white folks to suppress us. We brown folks do a fantastic job amongst ourselves. Absolutely shameful.

Please do not dine here. Staff used to be incredible but they are very rude and arrogant. Water was dropped on me and food was spilled without apologies. Nothing was done to remedy it and service was abysmal. Extremely arrogant servers who confidently sent the wrong items to your table and did nothing to help when notified of the mistakes. I used to come to this place last year but not the same. Go to Sahib or Bhatti on the same block instead

The reason why i gave all the 5 stars is for the hospitality, right from welcoming guests, taking order, serving food and suggesting they’re very exemplary in delivering a proper fine dining experience. We ordered Fish Amritsari, Pahadi Murg Kebab, Bhuna, Rumali Roti, Bone in Goat Biryani(Sauted, Not Dum), Rabri and Rasmalai.

I had been visiting Dhaba since 2010. In NYC I look no further than Dhaba NYC!  I like all food here: appetizers, veg and non veg.  Here are my favorites: samosa, cut mirchi bhajya, paneer tash ka ab, kadhai paneer, bhuna chicken, chicken balchao. The staff members: Jeevan, Ash, Vidur take care of me and know what I like, what spice level I like, what I like on the side.  Ambience is good and clean. I highly recommend this place to those looking for Indian food.
cozy little place food is alright. there starters are good
Love this Bay Ridge gem. Among the last of the excellent NYC bakeries. Worth the trip

Great food, heavenly dessert/pastry, friendly service & a warm inviting atmosphere. My special treat- Cannoli cream filled Lobster tail! Heavenly!! Thank you guys for making these for me this morning. I appreciate all who made this happen.

Their “amazing fruit infused iced tea served in a mason jar” is literally a small plastic cup of iced cold water with a tea bag thrown at the end. It tastes like tap water with 0 flavor and costs $7. Don’t get played like I did
Used to spend a lot there until they got political about the vaccine, they didn't have me, a good customer, and cancer patient in mind... never again
Great food, pastries and atmosphere.
It used to be amazing place with delicious desserts.
Friendly,  atmosphere with good, fresh food

This is such a cute little pastry shop/cafe. I stopped in today for a quick breakfast, and I was pleasantly surprised with the entensive menu that they have for such a small place. I opted for the Carrot Cake Pancakes, and for the price, they not only tasted really good, but they also gave a pretty good-sized portion for your monies worth. The one thing I found odd is that they serve food and beverages on disposable plates and cups. Otherwise, the establishment is very clean, and the service was very good. My server Carlos was very welcoming and friendly. I didn't get a chance to purchase any of the delicious looking pastries, but I will be sure to do so the next time I visit. 😋
Their pastries are over priced and stale.
Nice corner spot. Good customer service. Tried a few things, everything so far good.
Delicious variety.....
Definitely, I will come back for it. It’s one of the most delicious pastry.

The chocolate « croissant » is fantastic!! The size is generous and the blend of chocolate bar and chocolate cream is wonderful.
The almond croissant is quite decent.
The oat milk coffee was not great tho.
One of the best. Better than any other. The filling are delicious
Went for the bacon egg and cheese, it was horrible. The sandwich was 80% cheese and it was the only thing you could taste. I was so upset because I was excited to try it.

I live nearby but never went inside until I saw they had a thai tea eclair on their menu! The cream had a strong but not overpowering flavor of thai tea and had an amazing texture. It was very delicious :)

I visited this bakery later in the day on the weekend so they were out of some of their goods. I got the Raspberry danish and it was the best danish I've had in the city. it was full of vanilla bean cream and fresh sweet raspberries. I also tried the chocolate chip cookie which is a unique one because it's baked inside a tin making it perfectly round. I will absolutley be back to try more of their Danish flavors!

A small and amazing bakery offering freshly baked and delicately handcrafted pastries and desserts. The owner is also the chef. Petit Chou just recently celebrated their 4th anniversary!! It is a classic and “no-frills” bakery that is definitely worthy for a visit! We tried Egg and cheese quiche, almond croissant, and chocolate chip cookie. All are delicious!!
Delicious pastries!
Absolutely bussin. I mean this place is straight juice.
Place is gas. Cinnamon roll is straight juice. Might roll my way out of here after eating it but worth it.

This is a pretty small bakery. The desserts were delicious, lots of flavor and not too sweet. Went really well with a cup of tea the next day! Looking forward to returning and trying different flavors.

Who is paying for these positive reviews? This was the worst dessert I’ve ever had. The eclairs tasted like Walmart dessert that’s been left sitting on the counter for days. I’ve had better dessert from grocery stores. I would avoid this like the plague. My friends and I were excited to try such a highly rated spot after dinner, and were shocked at how bad these were.
So good! The banana cream pie and the bacon egg and cheese is a must! The chocolate chip cookie is to die for

As a pastry chef myself I was very excited to check this place out during my recent trip to NY. I ordered a Thai Tea Eclair and a Butter Croissant and both were horrible. The custard in the eclair was completely frozen in the middle and the choux itself was soggy and not enjoyable. The croissant was either a day old and refreshed or frozen and refreshed as well, disgusting. The only  employee was a young lady who showed zero interest in us as customers- she sat on her phone the entire time we were in the shop and texted - super unprofessional.

Overall if you’re looking for a premium patisserie experience in NY, this is NOT IT. Go somewhere where your $9 eclair is not frozen and where they bake fresh daily - somewhere where the FOH team is passionate about pastry instead of their cell phones. Go to Lysee, lol.

Definitely will not be returning and will be unfortunately recommending my peers to avoid this place during their travels.
Absolutely love the pastries here! We will definitely be back!
Very good croissants!
Delicious pastry

THRILLED to welcome Paris Baguette to Staten Island! The ambience is charming (HUGE space), and the staff is incredibly friendly. The pastries and bread taste especially fresh. I love their individual cake slices, which are always a hit. The attention to detail in both presentation and taste is evident. It's a wonderful addition to the community, and I look forward to making this my go-to spot for delightful pastries and a cozy atmosphere. Highly recommended!
Super friendly and chill vibe. Not to mention the pastries and sandwiches sooooo good! Loved it all.

I have been going to PB since its grand opening as I love their cakes. The cakes are always fresh and tasty. I have bought many cakes for my neighbors and they all love the cakes. After eating what I bought for them, many of my neighbors are now at PB every morning. Keep on baking great cakes for the Staten Island community.
This is one of the better Paris Baguettes in NYC. Great selection of pastries and everyone is nice and friendly. I’ll be back!

I'm very critical when it comes to good coffee, but this Paris Baguette did not disappoint! Not to mention, there are so many great options for bakery goods! My go-to's are soboro, red bean filled pastry, and egg tarts (and sometimes strawberry soft cream cake slices, if I'm in the mood)! If you're in the area, it's the best place for a quick grab-and-go!

Wow! It was about time Staten Island got its own Paris Baguette. The pastries are delicious and ordering the Strawberry Shortcake for events (birthdays and such!) is always a huge hit.

They’ve got such a large assortment of different goodies.

The selection of pastries is simply outstanding, with each item crafted to perfection. Whether you're craving a classic croissant with its buttery layers or a decadent fruit tart bursting with flavor, this Paris Baguette delivers on every front. Every bite is delicious and is a testament to the skill and artistry of their bakers, who infuse each creation with attention to detail. Their staff is always friendly and knowledgeable, ready to assist you in selecting the perfect treat for any occasion. A must-visit destination for anyone!

So happy that Paris Baguette is in Staten Island!! Lots of pastry and drink options & with lots of seating to enjoy your meal. My favorites are the almond croissant, raisin loaf bread, donuts, and croquettes. Their cakes are also a great option for birthdays and holidays. Great place for breakfast or even a late night dessert.
Cakes and pastries are good, although a bit pricey. Dining area could be cleaner; staff could be more friendly

Be ware! They charge sales tax for pastry.
That’s illegal.

Waaaaaay overpriced!!!!! Most of all there baked goods are store bought, just look at the packaging. $4 for a small regular coffe "for shame". Customers are shocked at the register when they find $12 for a plain croissant and a tiny slice if pizza, no beverage. The pizza is just terrible it has 3 slices of pepperoni, very dry and low,quality cheese. Support your favorite bakery that give a bit more just because they care. This is chain bakery, they don't care.

All bakery items are very delicious. However I ordered a cake and they told me they could write and customize the cake with whatever I liked. I asked for a simple “happy birthday mom” and this is what I received. I could have done the same thing and wrote it correctly instead of “happy mom birthday”
I love this place! Thank you for your service 😊

The only problem with the Paris Bagueete is that I wanted to order one of EVERYTHING!

The shop is beautifully and tastefully designed!  It’s well lit and spacious and the baked goods are displayed in showcases for close inspection and selection.

Even though it was 3 in the afternoon, they were constantly bringing out fresh items so the display cases were full and most importantly FRESH!

After careful debate on what four items we wanted, we were taken care of by a friendly and courteous staff member at the register.

We are going back tomorrow for an afternoon cappachino and another treat!

Welcome to Staten Island Paris Baguette, you were worth the wait!!!!!

This place has very good pastries, a little pricey for what it is but definitely delicious. What I dislike about this place is the cleanliness. I’ve gone here many times and almost each time, yes it’s busy but tables and dining area are a mess. There are always more than enough workers to come out and at least sweep the floors or wipe the tables in between each customer but most of them spend their time talking instead of actually working. It’s really a shame because again I do like this place a lot but they should do better with cleaning.

This bakery-gem is just around the corner. I cannot express enough how much I enjoy Raspberry croissants and Coffee Danish. Every time I bite a piece, I send grateful thoughts and positive vibes to all people who involved in their process creation. Thank you and have a good business, guys

I really hate to leave a bad review that would impact any business, but I'm so pissed.
I went today, the only person on the line, no one else in there. a cup of coffee took 15 min. which is fine they just forgot about it till they asked me what I'm waiting for, but it's ok. it happens, then I specifically asked for LACTOSE FREE LATTE. and I stressed it 4 times since I'm allergic to lactose, and I can't have it.
And when I was handed off the coffee, I also asked for the 5th time if it was lactose free and they said yes.
And unfortunately it wasn't!!! when someone asks for lactose free, PLEASE take it seriously. I'm not being picky, I end up with a lot of pain and have a very bad day fighting with the colon... THIS IS A SERIOUS MATTER. You need to be mindful.
Messed up my large coffee and giving me a small, which is fine
Have me waiting forever is also fine.
But I'm not having this.
Will no longer be a customer of this place anymore.

Very rude stuff , bad food never coming to this place again , worst treatment ever

My sis n son went in with a rude welcoming. We sat down n ordered neway, which took 4ever to get our food. Sis's food came wrong so they had to take it back. It was cold inside n not just the weather but atmosphere n staff. The food had a great deal of added sugar! I will not recommend nor eat here again! The restroom had a sign to keep it clean, but was dirty! I cleaned it as best I could b4 using. Very unhappy with this so called 4 star rated place.
Cute and friendly local spot!

When the pastries are fresh, they are of excellent quality. However, sometimes, the pastries are not fresh, resulting in a poor taste. The cakes I have obtained on several occasions were salty or sour. Despite the owner Josephine's claims that everything is baked daily, they are fully aware of having pastries that are several days old. Stay away from the pastries packaged in plastic by the window. I am disheartened by this lack of freshness in New York. Unacceptable. Josephine should be ashamed of herself for selling pastries that aren't fresh, especially when the prices are inflated. Go to Little Cupcake Bakeshop instead where the owners are proud of their craft.

Petit Chou is one of my favorite places in New York City. I live near by. I bring family and friends here all the time. I often walk by the shop and go in just to see what they have, even if I don't intend to get anything. Everything that is made here tastes as wonderful as it looks (and it all looks stunning).

The chocolate chip cookie is a must. While they keep a lot of their staples in consistent supply, they very frequently feature new items. Make sure to check in during the holidays (Thanksgiving, Mother's Day, Halloween, etc.) when they almost always have unique offers, many that require orders in advance that could feed a modest number of people. The staff is also was kind and professional. The space is small, but there are two separate counter areas with bar stools to enjoy your pastries.

This place is a true gem and a must for anyone that loves sweets!
Staff was very friendly, I got a slice of the mango cheesecake and chocolate croissant. Both AMAZING. Highly recommended and will be back

Very nice little spot!
Best chou in town!  Fresh tasting
Pistachio Eclair and Rose Lychee Choux soo good! Will try others pastries once I’m back in town. Everything looks tempting.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What Brought Me Here:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I came to the place because I saw a video of the croissant bacon egg and cheese sandwich (or how, they call it,  the "breakfast sandwich) and thought it would be a good meal.

After seeing the video showcasing the food on Instagram, I thought the place was going to be a local diner or deli, but to my surprise, it turned out to be a bakery.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What I Ordered:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-  Tres Leche Cake
- Croissant Bacon, Egg and Cheese ("Breakfast Sandwich")

* I had gotten a few more items, but these were the ones I remember the most when I bought their food.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
My Take:

Overall, the food was great, and I'll definitely go there again to grab some more. In my own opinion and consideration, it's definitely a spot that I would go to if I'm around the area, but not a place that I'll go the extra distance to travel just to have.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What I Hope They Update:

If they can, I would like them to update their website menu. It only shows some of the options they have at their establishment, and you'll miss out if you judge something based on what you don't see in person rather than checking it out from the online menu.

Literally just left but the service was so good I had to leave a review. It was my first time visiting this bakery and asked for some recommendation's. The staff member was very friendly and helped me pick some delicious treats for my sisters birthday, she even added some candles which was so sweet. I would definitely recommend and will be visiting again!

The bacon egg and cheese on the flat croissant was just amazing. I also added a strawberry cheesecake puff to go with it, and it was incredible also. I will definitely be back to try the other pastries and another croissant.
Awesome place.

I came on a Sunday morning and everything was still stocked. I got the pistachio eclair and chocolate hazelnut cookie.

Eclair: 4/5
The eclair was very very good, although the choux was a bit soggy and needed to be more crisp on the outside. The inside had an amazing soft texture though and was generously filled with pistachio creme that actually tasted like pistachio! The flavor made up for the texture.

Cookie: 3/5
The chocolate hazelnut cookie was good but not mind-blowing. The edges weren't crisp enough for me, but the inside was nice and gooey. There was some hazelnut butter spread throughout the cookie that made it really nice to eat, but there were also really large chunks of hazelnuts that made it not so pleasant. I wish more of the chocolate flavor came through, but overall, it was a good cookie, not too indulgent.

I'd try some of their other choux pastries (hopefully they'll have a better exterior), but I think I'd skip their cookies next time.
Everything here was sooo good and people are super nice also, will stop by whenever I visit!

I recently had the pleasure of trying Tres Amigos Taqueria & Restaurant's brunch, and I must say, it was an absolute delight! The moment I walked in, I was struck by the warm and inviting atmosphere. The decor is vibrant and colorful, with a lively vibe that perfectly complements the delicious food.

Speaking of which, the brunch menu at Tres Amigos is a real treat. I opted for the veggie wrap, which was generously filled with grilled zucchini, mushrooms, tomatoes, onions, and corn, all perfectly seasoned and served with a side of beans, rice, cheese, guacamole, and sour cream. It was a flavor explosion in every bite!

The service was also top-notch. Our server was friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable about the menu. The staff's enthusiasm and passion for the food they serve are genuinely infectious.

What truly sets Tres Amigos apart, however, is its commitment to using only the freshest ingredients. You can really taste the difference in every dish. Whether you're in the mood for something classic like tacos or carne asada, or something a bit more adventurous, Tres Amigos has got you covered.

In short, if you're looking for a fantastic brunch spot with amazing food, excellent service, and a fun atmosphere, look no further than Tres Amigos Taqueria & Restaurant. I highly recommend it!

*Rating:* 4/5 stars

*Price:* Reasonable

*Recommended for:* Brunch, Mexican food, casual dining

*Will I return?:* Absolutely!

Real fancy. 😉👍🥂 The atmosphere in the room felt like I stepped into the late 80's. I looked at their menu some meals were pretty expensive and some are not. There was a cup of water on the table when I got there and I used it for diet soda.🥤 I ordered the chicken parm hero with macaroni salad. 🥪🥗 All together with the soda is $21.00. I wasn't able to get the rest of it so I put it in a container for home 🏡. The group I was with had some issues with 3 people. One joke around, one craved attention and the other one got ambulance almost called because of a choking hazard 😔 pretty sad and I felt bad, but my day there wasn't too bad. It got settled. Maybe I'll come back one day for The full experience or maybe with a group that doesn't have these type of issues. 🙏😒🙂👍 P.S. I apologize to whoever I offended in this review. reviewText:
What a great night!!!!  Last night my business club had a private wine making class at Vino Divino.  Rob and his staff where extremely knowledgeable and so nice. The food was delicious and the wine was great.

The craziest part about my experience is that I personally know Rob for over 20 years.  Anytime I’ve needed anything from a donation to The Bini Fund or advice on a good bottle of wine he always took the time to educate me and never said no.
