placeName: Vino Divino Winery & School of Wine
reviewText: Definitely check this place out if you are a lover of wine. Rob, the owner, is not only generous but extremely knowledgeable and great to chat with. Fun times. Grab your friends and family and make a barrel.

placeAddress: 42 Industrial Loop E, Staten Island, NY 10309
placeName: Vino Divino Winery & School of Wine
reviewText: Rob Rispoli is a craftsman beyond his time.  We have been making wine with them for 4 years running.  Always a nice night out and the finished product is always perfect.  If you have been thinking about making your own wine definitely give these guys a call, you wont regret it.

placeAddress: 42 Industrial Loop E, Staten Island, NY 10309
placeName: Vino Divino Winery & School of Wine
reviewText: Great experience.  Have made several batches of wine there.  Robert Rispoli is the best!
Amazing food. The owners are so nice and attentive. They have a full dining room if you want to sit and dine.
The staff was really polite and attentive. The pizza was delicious and unique. I loved the atmosphere of the dine-in area. This is a great place to try if you're in the area.

Decided to try them again ordered meatball parmesan hero excellent sauce and meatball I live one block away. Food came in less than 15 minutes meatballs barely warm but the taste was excellent I asked for ricotta cheese it was still cold the bread us excellent  and mozzarella just  melted and nit even hot. Food tastes excellent but not heated . Hot heros should be hot. Not room temperature.  Next time make sure the foods hot
I never taste italian food typically italian.. amazing people, food and atomsphere.. highly recommended
Best pizza in Tottenville!!
Overall very good pizza and baked rolls are classic NY

I'm 63 years old, born in NYC and I had never been to Tottenville on Staten Island before today. So I headed over there, and decided to try the pizza at Mangia. Clean place, looked like they have a good crew. The pizza was Crispy! The sauce luscious with an occasional hit of oregano. I had a Sensational Staten Island Summer Saturday.
Friendly, welcoming staff and the food never disappoints!! Always delicious from start to finish!!
They make you feel like family

authorName: Thomas P Smith NY REAL ESTATE
reviewText: Mangia, Mangia, Mangia just added to the rotation. New to the area and wanted to try this place out. Heard all the locals go there. And now i know why. Pizza fantastic. Service was perfect they played nice Italian music while we ate. Perfect on pricing. Heres some photos of our time here.

Ordered dinner for pick up on 6/3. Ordered Mussels in red and white sauce, fried calamari, chicken wings and a white pie.
The best in the neighborhood from everything we have tried. My dad loved the red sauce, Fried calamari was crispy. Food was hot at pick up, the boy at the counter was so nice!
Thank you for the great food and service!
Unique pizza offerings and nice, cozy dining area
Always fresh and delicious!
Food was very good and the service was excellent

Oh my gosh this place is delicious !!  This is a must try place . The server was amazing and even the cooks were so nice and smiling from the back :) the food was so delicious !! The guacamole was some of the best I have ever had !! I don’t even like burritos but stole a bite of my boyfriends and it was sooooo good! I had the chicken quesadilla and would highly recommend that too !
There is a small kids menu also :)

Went back again and it was so good and got the pleasure of trying this cake right when it came out the oven . I was stuffed so the waitress put it in a to go box for me , but we tried a bit pretty much as soon as we got in home . It was so so so good!!  Delicious . Compliments to the chef !!

Nothing seemed authentic in the slightest. Elote had a dolope of crema or mayo sprinkled with some cheese. Esquites was more of a soupy dish. I paid for 1 taco as much as an order with 2-3 tacos. The beef tacos were placed with the pork in 1 dish. I was unable to eat because I was not the only one who ordered. If I had ordered 3 tacos it would've came out to $15+.... I wanted to try it
They do not answer calls for business if they do not answer

Had a little mishap where there were 2 separate orders with the same name. When my husband picked up the order, the lady confirmed the name but gave is the other person's order by accident. We went back to the restaurant and told them we got the wrong order and either wanted what we ordered or the $ back. We were all cordial about it. We paid $100 worth of food and received $40 worth of food by accident. They made us a new order and it was delicious. This will not affect us from ordering here again. We just need to check our order upon exiting next time.
Nice Mexican restaurant in Tottenville area. Reasonable price and food tastes delicious. Not that many options for drinks, basically Mexican sodas.
Great food! Great friendly service! The sangria is so good! Authentic Mexican food!
Good food
good birria tacos
I got the steak burrito and three tacos 10/10. absolutely delicious and authentic. Staff is also very friendly.
Ordered 2 chicken empinada. Made fresh not pre cooked . Even the chicken is not pre cooked. That chicken was so tender and moist. Best empinada I ever had. Looking forward to trying other food.

I just tried for the first time , and got nachos there was a misunderstanding and they came back with guac. Customer service was great and the delivery guy was sweet! We will order again! Pro tip get the beans on the side because they’re soupy , of course unless you like that on your chips . The food was fresh!
Fantastic food. Fantastic service. $4 Mexican Coca Colas?
The best bakery in Staten Island!

Every item i ever ordered here is top tier and beyond delicious. I stopped in on Christmas eve and even though i waited about an hour to order what i needed the front enclosure was very warm, beautiful smiling ladies walked around and offered coffee and pastries, and they even brought in a band to sing carols. This place knows how to cater to their customers and i will always love this place for that alone! 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼
Good
Bakery 🎂 🥮 🧁 🍰

The Royal Crown is my HAPPY PLACE!  Tonight I got a pork chop with sautéed spinach and I got my ice tea lemonade  and 2 pieces of grill chicken!  It was absolutely delicious 😋. Love Love this bakery!   ♥️♥️♥️♥️♥️

came here on a sunday with a friend around 11:30 we got two omelets, it is now 12:52 and we still were not checked on or were asked to receive a check. i enjoyed coming here previously, and i am not in a rush nor a normal complainer, but it looks like they are understaffed, service was very luck luster. but our waiter was very polite, i will never fault the wait staff. but my guest and i were very disappointed.
Loved the Royal cheese steak.  Very friendly staff!

Long lines for cookies that taste the same. Boy did the quality of the rainbow cookie go down. It's as big as a kids finger with no taste. Wish I had that 45 min back and that bill. Won't be going back. Looks like I will keep going back to Brooklyn going forward.  So sad to this place go down this year.
Food is amazing and prices are great!

If you like a Poor dessert go for the cute chocolate cup …. It’s just that a cup made of chocolate full of pastry cream only. Go for that. No cake, no cookie no nothing just cream and chocolate 🥲… very disappointed.
This is the home of my favorite salad and balsamic glaze!!

We first visited this place from a kind gentleman’s suggestion after my interview at the Staten Island Hospital.
We had absolutely a delightful experience there. What a hidden gem! We tried its grilled ribeye steak heroes and a hamburger. They were very delicious! And the Dessert!!! All kinds you could find there. We ordered two cakes to bring back to Manhattan. I am glad that this cafe is far away from my home, otherwise I would go eat at this place everyday!
I later went back many times traveling from upper west side to Royal Crown Cafe, always a satisfactory experience. I once had a chance to speak with its owner, such a gentleman, very warm and generous! Traditional Italian hospitality!
I look forward to enjoying good means at the place many more times to come…
Happy holidays to my beloved Royal Crown Cafe!
Excellent sandwiches. Great bread also!
I go here quite often for their cakes, fig walnut bread and I love their salads!  Fast service!  The freshly baked muffins are delicious!  Great service when dining in!
Great for catering, food is excellent.
Nice people and good food!
I went in to get two margherita slices, but the pizza had no flavor and the dough was floppy. I definitely wouldn’t come back here!! I’m better off making it at home myself
Stopped here for a quick slice between games and let me tell you how good it was, I don't have pics of garlic knots but best Garlic Knots I have ever had, next time trying there pastas
Greatpizza loved it ❤️
Just tried for the first time. Regular and Sicilian outstanding and great customer service. Website is easy to order also. Sorry I didn't try it sooner
Food 👍
Fantastic service and food.

Mangia is quickly becoming one of our favorite restaurants! The food is absolutely delicious, we haven't been disappointed with anything we've ordered so far! It's homemade and the portions are very large! The staff is friendly and the place is clean. Highly recommend
Wonderful restaurant.  Friendly wait staff. Food was delicious.  Had eggplant rolitini pizza.  Excellent! Worth a trip!

Food was really good! And huge huge servings!  ❤️ you can even share!
Waiter is very hospitable.. enjoying Italian music while eating! Mangia!

Additional info:
My 9 month old daughter was being fussy in the restaurant, the waiter gave her this ❤️ and she’s in love!  Very hospitable place indeed!
Very nice place .Food was very good.👍
Excellent chicken parm hero and service
Yum

I went to dinner with friends  and my fiancee..they love this place. I thought it was just ok...I had the stuffed artichoke which was cooked beautifully but eas not  seasoned enough. Then I ordered lasagna. So disapponted...the cook layered up sausage....I hardly tasted the pasta...no meat sauce and not enough cheese. They were kind enough to let me change my order. I then ordered a chicken Cesare salad which was very good. Their wait staff are very good which is why I said it was a four not a three.
Overall...it is good...not great.
Simple and wholesome. Nice neighborhood eatery
Everything we had was delicious

Excellent food! Everything we ordered was freshly made and delicious. The place is spotless, cozy and quiet just enough to carry on a conversation...and the service was exceptional. We're definitely coming back to Mangia's!
Real New York style Italian pizza. Big chunks of real sausage, real pepperoni and anchovies. So many fakes out there, it was great to finally have the real thing.

Fruit cheesecake is very delicious 😍👍🏻
Good prices
The pizza was excellent and the desserts were incredible.

For the life of me, I really don't understand it ? The food/pastry is bland at best . The clientele is like a line up of queer Gen Z'ers and their self absorbed,  metrosexual, disconcerting  parents, the service mediocre. The Staten Island bar has sadly once again been lowered.
Mix of Italian and Mexican Cucina. Friendly staff and food is amazing

Only my second time there.  Food is outstanding!  Service was great.
Reasonably priced menu.  Parking can be a little tough.

I ordered  shrimp  Parmesan sandwich and instead they send me chicken Parmesan when I called them they said that the same !!! No it’s not the same!! They are out of their minds Then other day I ordered bagel with bacon and eggs They gave me bagel with less than 2 strips of bacon and maybe 1and half egg The bagel was very skinny! And for this and ice tea I was charged  18$ and change  Ripe offs!  Watch out !
Just amazing overall.
The place is nice but quality of baked products has to be improved...
Great mexican food in bay ridge
Amazing food, especially their birria tacos. Portions are filling and they’re quick to make the food.

Went for lunch recently. We were the only patrons in the place at lunch. The service was not friendly, more like she lived there and was doing us a favor. Ordered quesadillas, not what I would expect a Mexican restaurant to serve, zero presentation, not sure if the photos in these reviews are real, but didn’t see one of those plates. The food was bland accept for the sauce she brought to the table, said “here’s mild and hot” there was nothing mild about it, they were hot and hotter. Food looked like it was thrown on the plate and that’s it. Would not return. Oh and the menus are a joke, printed paper with all the prices sharpies out, so you have no clue how much the bill will be
Worth the price, quick with preparing our order. Will eat again

Tried this place for the first time today, needed a new place in the area for lunch! Coworker and I got the 3 birria tacos with consommé and spicy chicken burrito. Both dishes were delicious! Everything tasted very fresh and prices were good too. Will be back to try more!
They catered my wife's 60 the birthday party for Cinco de mayo the food was amazing everyone wanted to know where the food came from 3 amigos did a fantastic job the food was so delicious ty 😊
As always great food and great service! A must try spot! Very friendly staff.
Food is excellent,very fresh,authentic and full of good flavor,
Solid fish tacos. Great service
Always a pleasure coming here.   Chorizo Quesadilla is absolutely amazing
I loved it. Food was great, and the staff very friendly.

Great dishes with other mature customers. Owners walk around greeting all. Very pleasant. Skirt steak special and the burrito was delicious. Thoroughly enjoyed a pitcher of their of red sangria.
They also can do traditional Hondurian dishes with a few days notice. We plan to place a large order of baleadas & horchata for a family party soon.

One of my favorite restaurants in Tottenville! Amazing homemade food and one of the best red sangrias I ever had! During the summer they also make mango and coconut sangria which is beyond delicious! Try this place you won’t be disappointed!

Definitely the best spanish restaurant in the area with very delicious food. Everything was fresh and prices were very fair. Great dining experience and the service was excellent as well. Highly recommended especially if you want authentic and wholesome food while supporting entrepreneurial businesses during these challenging times.

This is my favorite Staten Island Mexican restaurant. The food is amazing. For appetizers we had the nachos supreme, the stuffed sweet plantain and for my main  I had the steak tacos. It’s three tacos but my picture only has two because the food  was just so tasty I rushed to eat it before taking pictures. The service was great, very friendly and welcoming.
No way I can go through Brooklyn and not stop. Must have
Obnoxious sign in the window that they don’t “discriminate” against unvaccinated people.

This food was absolutely INCREDIBLE. Hands down one of the best breakfast meals I’ve ever had in Brooklyn. Their vegetable omelette is DIVINE. Their pancakes are DIVINE. Please order from here if you’d like to have a nice breakfast with your partner on a Saturday morning. You will not be disappointed. Thank you!

Walked in and was offered no services. Asked 5 times for assistance. Just plain RUDE. A horrible overall experience. After tasting the cake, I got more upset. The slices were not cheap but I assure you cake from Costco tastes better.
Great job! Thank you!
Delicious food and kind staff - thankful for their stance and their nondiscriminatory policies. 👏🏻
Excellent pastries and food. Best rainbow 🌈 cookies in the world. Friendly and attentive staff. I highly recommend.
Amazing place

Lovely place to set enjoy a cup of coffee , breakfast or lunch. Easy going yet pretty and thought out . Detailed menu with reasonable prices and friendly staff.
Revisited this bakery recently and staff is not wearing masks at all with an obnoxious sign in the window. Sad that it come to this, politics over safety.
This place rocks!

Will support this place for the rest of my life
Also great Italian pastries!
This Place was amazing! The food was awesome and the service was great. Can’t wait to visit again!

I will definitely support this biz. I’m going to go sit down to eat without having to show a pass. They do not discriminate and I applaud them. If you don’t like it, mind your biz and don’t go. Plenty of other biz that don’t have the balls to stand up to tyranny. Kudos to them!!

We catered food for our sons birthday. Everything was amazing! We ordered Chicken Marsala, Linguini w/ White Clam Sauce, Penne Vodka, Sautéed Spinach, Caesar Salad, pizza & a tray of garlic knots (the best). Everyone was raving about the food. My only regret is that I thought to take pictures half way through eating. I would highly recommend Mangia to anyone looking to cater an event or simply have an awesome meal!
I love it... it's better than other restaurants around here... food is delicious, prices are fair and service is top notch.
Lovely setting, good service, just ok food.
Just ordered a pizza from them boy was it good crust stayed crunchy the whole time that never happens on delivery
Owner came over to table a few time to chat with us.Waiter was excellent.Food is excellent.We sat outside great outside seating.You must visit for a meal.

Great food, very reasonable priced,
The owner over sees every dish,
Food is always great. The staff is amazing.
Very good...

By far one of the best Pizzeria/Italian eatery’s in all of Staten Island.  The food is always amazing and on point. Warm and friendly staff , clean and comfortable. Why does this place not have a Michelin Star?
The only bad part… is that everyone on the north shore has no idea that this place exists. Definitely worth the train ride and the short walk!
Great food and great service, octopus and shrimp oreganata is unbelievable
Peter the owner is a great host.He loves his patrons,this Is a can't miss.

Amazing, fresh, authentic Mexican food! The service was amazing and the frozen margaritas were to die for. I wish I could give this place 10 stars if was honestly amazing. They treated my kids and us amazing I can’t wait to go back
Lovely people, good food and service
Nice environment and excellent service.
The food was very delicious, I ate a very delicious roast beef, excellent Don César.
Excellent place, good food and good drinks, and good service and the owner is an excellent person, come and enjoy with your family. I recommend this place it's good

My family and I are always ordering meals from this place, they got some of the best burritos and tacos, specifically their al pastor tacos mmmmm. Delivery is always great, the food is hot and the employees are nice. Requests are always obliged to when you order online which is very nice. Absolutely love this place, it is worth the occasional splurge. Try it now!!

*in the picture is the Burrito San Cabos with a mango sauce, shrimp,rice, etc. it is sooooo good 😊

Excellent food
Great service good price love the family adtmosphere
Just great
Good food. Great staff. We'll be back.
Local Mexican restaurant, delicious hot food, attentive servers, what's not to like?  I recommend this restaurant!
Best good in thr area! Delicious!
Food is excellent and staff is friendly.

Very Clean and Nice Looking inside. Very friendly and great service. The drinks are . Very Nice Menu. Great Prices. The food came out hot and freshly made. The Steak and Chicken was cooked perfect. I loved the Mexican Ice Cream and Churros.
This place is awesome! Beautifully decorated and nice and cozy! Great food and fantastic service! Highly recommend!!
The food was good the service was excellent especially Tuesday and Thursday 11 a.m 🫡😋😘
Food was good, service was good, definitely would go back. I got a cheese burger medium rare and was cooked perfect. The fries were nice and crispy.
Horrible food. Better with the last chef.
Dry burgers, tasteless wings. Not as good as it use to be
Dry tasteless food. Heard it used to be good but haven’t had good food yet.
Cool neighborhood bar with mostly locals. Has a good kitchen too
Went here tonight for dinner, the service was amazing, such a nice waitress we had!!! Food was very good! Overall very pleasant experience

Because your menu was so limited WE went next door and brought pizza slices back sat at YOUR bar and had cocktails.  The bartender was so nervous the OWNER would be all over HER cams?  Imagine?  She should be awarding her staff for their CONSCIENTIOUSNESS in CARING for HER customers and NOT worrying about having a slice.  What happened to CARING about EACH other’s wellbeing?  Your staff is professional.  They are NOT competitors.  Professional rapport?  How about having a professional relationship?
Been coming here for years, awesome owner and great staff. Can’t beat it. Beer is cold people are genuine.

First time ordered from W’s and very disappointed.  The order was placed outside door with no indication it was there, no text no knock on door.  The items ordered were not good especially the hamburger platter, the meat was not a fresh chop meat burger but a frozen flat hardly cooked burger.  Will not make that mistake again with this restaurant,$75 for a meal that had to discard and the shrimp in a basket was so tiny shrimps all bread
The service is great bartenders are great.
Our server/bartender was and is always the best!  Very attentive! We enjoy coming here and come as often as we can. Keep of the good work W’s!

I had a great evening on my own sat at the bar.
Fantastic mussels and absolutely perfect fries!

Local spot for after work for drinks and late night dining. Spot is a gem, open late and the drinks taste amazing and does the job!! Nice buzz, cool vibe and good food. I always order an Amaretto Sour, I heard the wings hit and the Turkey Chilly is cool.
Great irish pub with great food!
Great old school pub. Friendly service. Fun atmosphere. Great place to watch the games. Food was also impressive. Had the curry fries and they were amazing!
Brooklyn Public house
Great neighborhood pub with friendly professional staff.  They have a good selection of beers and bar food.
Damián the bartender and Jack the server were great!

Stopped here for lunch during Christmas and New Year’s. It was really busy but we were able to find 2 seats at the bar. There was only one member of staff working but she did a great job of serving so many people.

We ordered the fish and chips, chicken club and a side of curry sauce. The food was delivered pretty quickly and everything tasted good. The curry sauce was slightly sweeter/fruitier than we are used to but it wasn’t a bad version of UK curry sauce.

There were a couple of football (soccer) games on and the bar was really buzzing on a Monday afternoon. A really fun spot to watch some sport and have some good pub food. We live locally and will definitely visit again.

Only place I go to catch a local VIBE
Top tier in every way, any day
Proper rare burger, hot chips, & house ale never disappoints

Was glad this place was open earlier to see an EPL game. My friend and I were looking to order the burger and beer combo but the waiter said they weren't serving lunch so we looked at the brunch options. Just a few moments later we saw other people receive lunch items like the burger and calamari.

We saw the bottomless brunch option and it looked like a good deal since we were already going to order a brunch item and a drink or two. I asked the waiter if it came with a brunch item and he said "yes it's included" so we went with it since it looked like a better deal. After we finished and saw our bill we were shocked to see that we had to pay the $22.00 on top of our brunch orders. A waitress told us that she always clarifies that the brunch item is not included so we felt cheated by the first waiter who said the brunch item was a part of the deal. Please reword your menu to make it more clear what the customer is paying for.
vying for (one of the) best Guinness in Brooklyn. Nice relaxed vibe.
The food is good
Guinness and Christmas dinner like back the old country
Upscale bar food in a mad cozy spot! They accommodated our group of nine and Jack provided great service the whole time!

love the staff, service is great. The negative is the manager yells at the staff and bartender in front of customers which is very unprofessional and created a negative environment and therefore a negative experience. very unprofessional.
Good food and brews.
The cheesesteak egg rolls are to die for. My absolute favorite. The kitchen is open late during the week unlike most restaurants in the area which is amazing.
Delicious food in a nice atmosphere. It's great to have a spot like this in Tottenville.

The place was really nice, great staff, no waiting. The burgers were incredible and the fries were beyond my expectations!

Will go again!
I hope the new owners change the food!!! I have to drive across S.I to Duffy s for a great burger & wings. I am hoping for big changes with the food!!
Lots of fun, good burgers and more
Great food
Cozy neighborhood bar. Nice food and drinks. Always, always packed 😊
Good burger, plenty of TVs
Great burgers!!!
Love my burger
Great food very family oriented great staff

Oh my goodness,
this bar is such an oasis of joy.
I have felt the warmth of true welcome.
A place of solace and truth.

I was here for a dog’s birthday party. A dog I adore. This was a place where celebrations were abundant. Just breathing the air was being transported to Utopia.

The Brazen Head is not to be missed. It’s to be enjoyed.

Came for my friends 4 year dog adoption anniversary.  Despite allowing 8 dogs in the patio which I LOVE, they denied me entry because I had a 10 month old?!?  Nonsensical and was very dismissive about the whole thing and wouldn’t even let me see my friends to just say goodbye like a human being.  👎

Loved this bar.  It is a good size space.  Emma, the bartender, was great.  It feels like a neighborhood bar but very welcoming.  The prices are good.  It is very laid back and the people I met here were very friendly.  I will definitely come back.
Surprisingly decent prices for drinks. Fantastic local. Dart board and board games to boot.
A sports bar like we wanted it. They weren’t diffusing the game we were looking for but still had a great time. The waitress was helpful and the atmosphere pleasant. A good time with friends !
Saw Lulu handle a difficult customer with grace and had a great conversation with customers after the fact. Always enjoy coming here for the great deals.

(Nov 2014) A quiet pint on a very cold Sunday arvo. I felt like a real American, sitting up at the bar, sipping away and enjoying the lack of punters. Nice friendly feel. 15 taps, nothing mind blowing but more than good enough. Pricing good ($7 pints) and I love the fact they disclose the keg tap date. As others have noted more emphasis on the hard stuff; 20 single malts, maybe 30 bourbons and 20 ryes. Good setup but won’t be the first stop for geeks.
I like this vibe. Old fashioned tastes very great. The background music is a little bit noisy but everything is great.
Our bartender was really personable! It was my husband's first time in the city, so the bartender had a great energy listening to his stories of being in "the big city." The toddies were delicious!
New York is cool
Went on a rainy Saturday night for a cold beer. Lots of choice and friendly staff, but pretty dead, I guess because of the rain. Seems they are dog friendly which is always a plus for me.
Great Bar to have a beer and just chill.
It's always good to come back here to familiar settings, esp w the area changing so drastically.

I love this bar normally but I recently had an awful experience with one of the male bartenders who verbally berated me. He was a tall man with short hair wearing a baseball cap and he was relentlessly rude to me which was both extremely unnerving and disrespectful. I’ve never been treated that way at this bar before and I would hope that management sees this and knows who I’m talking about so they can deal with this bartender who should not be in any kind of service industry.
Very cool vibe inside- love the wood, the stained glass, all the candles, etc. Quite crowded on a Friday night ~9
Rude bartender and overall unsettling vibe.
Love this place 😍
Amazing place with perfect bartenders

Be aware!
I Rarely write reviews; however my visit, to Brooklyn Inn left me unsettled and shocked as I observed a long haired bartender displaying aggressive and intimidating behavior, towards a patron.The bartender demeanor was shockingly impolite, unprofessional and extremely aggesrrive. Almost bordering on the side.

The customer appeared courteous and composed. Was visibly disturbed and emotionally affected by the behavior they experienced.This kind of treatment is completely inappropriate and intolerable, in a setting such, as a bar where individuals gather to relax and have a time.

I find it concerning that a person who displays such a temper is permitted to interact with customers as part of their job responsibilities. This particular occurrence has left me with a bad perception and I will never recommend this business unless appropriate measures are implemented toward the guy behind the counter. It is unjust for anyone to be subjected to behavior.
The seats by the window could be cleaner,lots of empty glasses and human detritus.
Wow!! Goddamn.Is this bar my heaven? Yes. Thanks Chris
Wonderful staff. Great ambiance. Fantastic drinks. What else could you ask for? Daniel and Chris are best bartenders in the world!!!!!! Cmon down
Great food and atmosphere
Great service and they open late!
Chill spot
The best for as long as I can remember

My 1st experience....great staff nicki,Keri
Enjoyed my deluxe burger
And great conversation
Would not hesitate to return
And recommend to all good neighbors
Very homey
CHAZ
Excellent staff is phenomenal
Great Father's day dinner and drinks with the family!

Great place to go after work; they don't have a kitchen but you can bring your own food and the bartenders are awesome. Emma and Matt are always amazing. Drinks are variant and the prices are doable for a poor man :)

Drinks are good and strong. Bartender was able to make drinks for a group of about 20 plus other patrons with no problem. They don’t have food but you are able to bring in your own food. Overall good bar to check out. I believe they also have an outdoor space.

I’ve been going to The Brazen, with my wife, for decades and it never disappoints.
It’s now run primarily by Emma and Tray and you’ll be hard pressed to find better bar staff aligned with a traditional bar like Brazen. I.e. this isn’t a cocktail bar (although they’ll make you a fine Old Fashioned etc), but it is a very welcoming, warm bar-with reasonable prices and a great line up of beer’s/spirits.
Expensive, rude / accord bartenders
Great backyard, good drinks

Matt the bartender is amazing! Had a bad experience at a bar down the road and choose to come here Instead and it was the best decision we’ve ever made. Will be coming back solely for him, asset to the bar :)
Good place to grab a beer
Always been one of my favorite parts, what a nice dive it is.
Great bar, good prices and lovely bartender. Thank you John
only lager during happy hour
Great night we had, thanks Can!
Great place to come after playing tennis at Fort Greene
Great local pub
Very nice bar with good food and great cocktails. It’s a great atmosphere and if you look closely it has some super dope decor.

The bar seemed nice at first but after our group (about 10 ppl) got settled and was in the middle of talking, the music suddenly became very loud we couldn’t hear each other. We asked the bartender and was told that it’s a matter of policy - if there was a certain amount of ppl in the bar the music had to be loud. People just started leaving because there’s no sense in hanging around when you couldn’t hear anyone talk including yourself. I’m just confused why music volume has to be a rigid rule when there were only 20ppl in the bar and everyone was clearly uncomfortable with the sound level?

Worst bar in Brooklyn with horrible service. My girlfriend had fireball dumped on her skirt by a worker after he shoved her out of the way for no reason after she had just arrived sober and would've moved if asked politely. Bar interior is awfully configured and drinks are expensive for what is essentially a glorified dive bar. Would recommend any other bar.

Drinks good; the location awesome; the crowd cool; the prices right for cocktails, beer, and wine. The wine is actually very good, better than a lot of others in this lovely hood, especially for the price in a time where there's too many blah meh wines out there for 14 plus dollars. Mind you, the food is pub food except for the cheese plate that should satisfy most any appetite for its ample portion and quality cheeses. The service is relaxed; the mood, cozy. So don't be uptight about waiting when it's busy--so just the right snug for a cooler crowd.
My favourite bar in Brooklyn. Great service, awesome burgers, perfect IPAs. Try the Flower Power
This is my go-to place in Brooklyn! The food is always good. The burger is perfection.  The boards are always fresh and delicious.  It's definitely a place I visit often!
Always enjoy the food and friendship thereat. A great place to mingle.
Nice place with good lunch but they stop serving too early.
Quiet place for a drink and game
Stopped for a couple drinks. Good decor. Nice crowd.
Great people. Great service..clean safe place
Still a great local bar. Nicely refurbished.
Best burgers ever!
Good

Lovely place for a late night pint. The kind of bar staff you wish every establishment could have.

Was really excited to go to this inn however atmosphere was ruined but the most rude excuse for a human we where shouted at from as we entered we had seen reviews on the barkeepers preferences as we where from  South Africa we where not welcomed friendly therefore we hid in the back as we didn’t want  the barkeeper to ruin our night however she proceeded to follow us and scream at us no matter where we went it is a shame because the building is stunning however the owner is keeping staff there that ruin the whole experience would not recommend to anyone until the barkeeper has been fired
Great neighborhood bar. Really nice staff. Gets crowded on weekends but a perfect place to grab a pint on weekends!
Went here with my girl friends late on a Sunday night & the drinks were amazing! The bartender was super nice & the vibes were so cozy. Highly recommend!
The most beautiful place i've ever seen....
They them weirdo spot, 8 dollar beers. Ooof

The ambience and decor of this establishment is amazing, but it is quite misleading. The bartender here is extremely rude and short tempered. Based on previous comments she seems to have a disliking towards certain people of color and is a "little" racist.

Stay blessed
Bartenders have polite humor and friendly vibes! great spot to catchup with old friends and shoot pool!

When me and my girlfriend spontaneously walked into The Brooklyn Inn for some Moscow Mules we were pleasantly surprised with the quaint and swank ambience inside. Unfortunately our experience was spoiled towards the end of the night due to the bar tenders insolence. We first witnessed the bartender shouting and swearing at customers (albeit they did appear difficult customers). As it was last orders I had politely said excuse me (since I wanted to check that there was enough time to play a game of pool) and in response the bar tender threw his finger up at me, not letting me even finish, turned around to everyone at the bar and indirectly ridiculed me for trying to get his attention. It is a great shame the night had ended like this as we would have liked to come back but due to the impertinent and childish behaviour witnessed we will not be returning.
Old timey bar. Good beer selection. No specialty drinks or happy hour specials. Great vibe though. Good people
They carded at the door which is fine. Needs more seating. Overall cool vibes.

Sometimes you find the perfect happy ending to a hard day of vacationing, and this was that place for my friend and I. After putting many miles on the feet, we arrived here to find good drinks and great company. Best bar experience in awhile. Cheers
I love the pastrami and corned beef sandwiches here friendly staff
Good friendly place, I love to go for lunch
Great Burgers. Fast service. Nice bar.
always a pleasure, relaxed, friendly and best burgers but you might have to expand soon
Great atmosphere
GREAT PLACE

I was here last weekend to have a late dinner (arround 8:30). Me and a friend sat at one of the small tables near the bar. We were ignored for about 15 minutes before the waitress came over and took our drink and appetizer order. We didn't receive our drinks for almost another 15 minutes and then it took almost another 40 minutes for wings and pretzels to come. The service was so bad and everything took so long we didn't bother to order a main course. The food wasn't worth the hour and a half we were there.
Great food

Great staff. Best French Onion soup in town. Great burgers, and the fries are cut fresh. Can't beat it if you wanna sit at a bar and have a burger.

I popped in for a drink with hubby. The Great Georgiana is a chill spot. I found it to be a perfect place for me to people watch while sipping on a perfectly made Aperol spritz and enjoy hubby drinking Jamison neat.
Great cocktails and food!
Very chill, laidback bar. Came in early and had a cocktail and read a book. Wasn’t too busy. Good service.
There are some exceptionally great DJ's here on a monthly basis.

authorName: Same old New York New Solutions

reviewText: Very cute bar - the ceiling decoration, attic and fan is giving me southeast Asian vibe and love it
Best burger I've eaten in New York for a reasonable price

Came here just for evening drinks on a Wednesday night. It was a very relaxed and cozy setting with lots of space outside. Both inside & outside available. They were understaffed so service was very slow! I got my espresso martini & it was truly amazing. So highly recommend. Other people's drinks were good as well from what I heard.
It's a nice spacious corner restaurant. But I felt like there was no staff & the place had no direction.  There's food & drinks avaliable.
Brooklyn Draft Beer is super tasty! It’s a regular to have that.
Nice Personel and good beer at fair price..

No food ordered, just after work drinks w coworkers. Had not patronized this spot in years. They have a really cool board game (& darts) section w a sofa, and I believe an outdoor back patio. Drinks were, eh ok (measured pours and too much ice), but they have a great variety of middle to top shelf choices.
Really nice bar on Atlantic
most attentive staff, cleaniest coziest dive bar in the world
Chill, cosy pub for drinks & games. The bartender was super lovely & friendly! Recommend for a chill one if you're in the area.

The atmosphere here is pretty dope. TVs all around and sports were playing. It's loud but no louder than the average bar - and that was more so because people were cheering for their winning basketball team. But it's pretty cozy here otherwise. Comfy lounge area, nice ambiance/lighting, and very chill. If you're looking for a spot to chill or hole up in, this is definitely it! My friend had a virgin margaritas 🍹 it was pretty good.

I was especially happy with both bartenders that I encountered (shift change); professional, kind, and helpful. Discovered a back porch area when heading to the restroom; headed out there to find a wonderful group of patrons and hung out. A really good experience on all counts.

Want craft beers in Brooklyn? This is the place!

Knowledgeable staff and a good selection.
Large selection of beer.
Happy Hour from 4-7pm Monday to Friday. Their happy hour Margarita is legit. There is even a small garden out there.
Great ambiance, great beer and great staff. What else do you need?
Fantastic environment!!

A really relaxed and cozy setting with lots of space outside. They were understaffed so service was a bit slow, but the drinks were good. The best part of coming here is just walking down Dekalb on a breezy Saturday night in summer. There are string lights everywhere, people dining or drinking outside on every corner - just a great buzz to the neighborhood that feels like you could be in Europe! If we stopped allocating so much NYC street space to cars there could be a whole lot more of this!
Great cocktails, but seemed like they were a bit understaffed. Also AC was not working inside so it was quite warm.

Our veggie burgers were not hot, and they were way undercooked. Too much onion was piled on top, but the onion wasn’t caramelized as advertised but rather it was clear gelatinous mush. Salad was very basic, only lettuce l, Parmesan and cranberries. Overall our food was quite disappointing. No AC available indoors.
A neighborhood standard. May this place never close
This is a nice place to stop and grab  a bite and a drink. Small on the inside. But cozy. Wings are a very nice size.

People working the bar have no sense.  I'm ready to put in my drink order and bar order.  He's like I just need your drink order. Why can you not take both are you also going to be the one working on my food? Of course not and the place is busy so why should you not take the full order.  Then I don't have to wait longer to get my food. For a place in the city operations should not be inefficient.
One of my favorite places in the neighborhood. Cocktails are great (especially the Egyptian Shumba) and a great burger.

Literally my favorite bar over the years. Incredible music, good food, consistently good drinks, and excellent outdoor seating. Bar staff has always been really nice. During COVID times their outdoor accommodations have been really great - fully outdoor spots for the more conservative, and a heated outdoor/indoor spot for those on the fence (all outdoor spots very dog friendly). Always a great hang.

I've been on the lookout for COVID-safe bars, and The Great Georgiana certainly fit the bill. The tented outdoor seating area has heated lamps so you can huddle in your winter jacket and sip on vodka, Russian-style.

Somewhat unseasonably, I ignored the bartender's suggestion of the hot toddy and went with the Slim Fittins (Tito's vodka, basil, lemonade). Yeah, I was basically drinking lemonade in 40 F weather. Having sufficiently frozen my fingers, I replenished my blood circulation with the house red and kind of wish I just had two glasses of it and called it a night.

Nice place to catch up with friends or coworkers you've not seen since the dawn of face masks. My former colleague and I went on a Wednesday evening around 6:30, and it wasn't crowded at all.
Amazing cocktails! Have tried half the menu and all are great!

STOP I freaking LOVE this place. (coming from a 21 year old) GREAT 60's-80's music (Cher *chefs kiss*), the people! here! are! wonderful! They are so kind, so cool (in every way; look, vibe, swagger, kindness, etc). The drinks here are beautiful. I recommend the tequila drink with hot honey, and the mezcal drink with the pepper. So Good! Thank you for a wonderful Saturday night evening!
Service was excellent and there was a good mix of tables outside.
Good drinks. Good atmosphere.

Ok look, I NEEDED this burger, I didn’t know I needed it, but I see the light. It was perfect. Meat seasoned to perfection; a cheese slice that provided full-patty coverage. The pickles weren’t no run of the mill pickle, but a fresh, slightly sweet pickle.

It wasn’t sloppy, but stood firm with a generously thick patty. This burger is the bees knees.
Try the Hamburgers and Tortilla Española!.
Fun spot, good drinks, great burger.

The food was satisfactory, and the atmosphere was excellent. Enjoying the outdoor seating during pleasant weather is highly suggested. However, with only one server attending to more than eight tables outside, some items were overlooked, and the service lacked attentiveness overall.

The bar offers an excellent selection of drinks that pair perfectly with the flavorful menu. I particularly loved the relaxed vibe of the outdoor seating, which made for a perfect evening. While the burger was satisfying, the standout dish for me was the panisse, thanks to its unique and bold seasoning that added an unexpected twist to the meal. The combination of great food, drinks, and atmosphere makes this spot a must-visit.

The service was friendly and attentive, adding to the overall pleasant experience. The drink menu offered a nice selection of local beers and creative cocktails that paired well with the food. I also appreciated the laid-back vibe, which made it a perfect spot for both casual dinners and catching up with friends. If you’re looking for a cozy yet lively place with delicious bites, this is definitely worth a visit.
Very tasty food. I recommend!
Pretty mid - would avoid.  Food decent but overpriced and service is terrible
The deviled eggs taste like salad dressing :) So good. Inga’s bar nearby is also good. Both places are good!

Unpleasant service. All the waitresses stared at us because we weren't dressed like bobos in shirts and polo shirts. We were almost refused entry because we had our cute little dog. The waitresses wanted us to leave quickly, so they threw the bill at us to get us out of the way. Ashamed !

good cocktail if you don't look at the price.
discriminatory. we got a makeover from all the staff. They first wanted to refuse us entry because I had my dog, but could not because he is a service dog. I then saw that dogs were allowed, we just weren't welcome.
They then threw us out and threw us the bill after 30 minutes.
brief poor service
I love how casual and unassuming yet fun this bar is. It’s a great spot to meet with friends for a really solid drink.

Last night we went to attend a relative's birthday party. A table of 12 was reserved. Once the table was full and a few other guests started to arrive, the hostess confronted our cousin at the table and demanded to know how many more people were expected. As it was unclear, we asked if any of the other tables were reserved in the back room and if they were available or if we could split off and have some of the party sit at the bar. The hostess responded that if there were more than 12 people, we were required to rent the whole back room at an additional cost. She added that we weren't allowed to stand around in the back room and to stay out of the way of her wait staff. She came back 15 minutes later, making the same speech in front of the whole room.

I understand the limitations of running a business in such a small place and the importance of organization and scheduling reservations to maintain some sense of order and flow for the kitchen and staff, but to repeatedly embarrass and humiliate your guests with such arrogance, hostility, and condescension is unforgiveable.

If our cousin misunderstood the rules or even if she was blatantly ignoring them, the hostess should have pulled her aside in private for that conversation.

Appalling, unprofessional, and disgusting behavior. I'll never go back.
It was hot and musty there

Watching the guys play  Dart was amazing.

Moot is a great neighborhood bar. To me, the Wednesday trivia is perfectly calibrated by the host, Josh. The bartender, Chaz, has been there 10 years and is an efficient pro and a good guy to trade war stories with. A pint is $7-$8. What more do you want in a bar?
Great place great friends

mod $

Good time!

Casual and chill neighborhood bar with a wide beer selection. They even gave me a water bowl for my dog, which I appreciated. I spent $8 per beer, which I found to be a bit higher-priced. Note that they have a $15 minimum for credit cards. Service was just okay, my bartender seemed annoyed when I was trying to get her advice on what to order (I noticed she was being a lot more friendly with the male customers). All in all, this seems like a place for beer lovers but I personally do not plan to be a frequent customer given the lackluster service.

Great outdoor area set up. It's on a wide sidewalk so I didn't feel like I was eating in traffic. Pretty good drink options, and appeared to be pet friendly.

Love this place my go to local bar. While on my daily dog walk I occasionally stop by to pick up one of their frozen margaritas (real juices) with a cup of fries (lemon salted)

A must try. Perfect on a warm sunny day
Drinks great,  environment and music owesome
The best place in Brooklyn

I have very mixed feelings about this place. The cocktails are very good. The food is meh. The cheese curds are amazing and not to be missed, but I would skip the burger. I don't understand all the raves it gets -- mine was sickly gray and overcooked. It did come with some pretty stellar fries though!  I love the kitschy mid-century modern decor, from the neon "BAR" sign out front to the 1930s/40s-era backbar and the cozy vinyl-upholstered booths. I particularly loved the busty pinup gal lamp on the backbar. I had plenty of time to take a mental inventory of all the period details because we waited more than hour to be seated. "You're next on the list" the hostess said, as she sat one table, then another, then another until we politely pitched a fit, which quickly got us both an apology and a table.

Burger is NOT what it used to be. The patty seems very different and lacks the depth of flavor that the burger once had. Super disappointing because I would have said previously that this place has the best burger in town.
Cute little bar with a diner feel. Sat at the bar, bartenders were very attentive. Dim lights, and great cozy atmosphere. Would come again.
lazy
Always a pleasure to visit for some of the best cocktails and possibly the best burger in NYC! Great wait staff and bartenders and an eclectic playlist in a setting from another era. Lots to love!
I wish I could give this bar 11 stars
Had a great night with friends, thank you for taking care of us!

I am once again begging Long Island Bar to make a veggie burger 🙏 there are basically no good veggie burgers in the neighborhood anymore and I would come here weekly instead of monthly if they put a veggie burger to the caliber of HiHi Room's (r.i.p.) on the menu! Until then, the best vegetarian dinner here is the gem salad with a side of deviled eggs and I *will* keep coming back for it.
Five stars regardless, love this place. Even if it gets a bit "scene-y" (you can kind of tell when someone has posted a TikTok blowing up the spot lol) Long Island Bar is true to itself and never wavers.

Overall, this place is just fine. Nothing unique (maybe the decor- they have old school diner decor) and nothing on the menu that’s AMAZING and worthy of a recommendation.

We had the burger, trout, and gem salad.

The gem salad was just a Cesar salad (no little gem, straight up romaine) with some radishes and a few pumpkins seeds. It was a fine salad, no complaints

Burger was just fine.

Trout was cooked nicely but had no flavor and the potatoes it came with were under cooked.

Racist establishment. Refused to seat me at the bar, telling me the stools were in use, a white couple came in immediately after and they were given the seats instead. If you patronize this bar you condone racism.

The Strawberry Margarita was soooo strong i had one sip and just left it there. Undrinkable. We ordered food as well, The Mac and Cheese was tasteless and so small not Worth the $13. We also got the Grilled cheese it was Okay. Not great. Over all the outdoor seating was nice but not coming back.

Super chill. Try the "Ella Fitzgerald"

Great freaking Burger!!

Good vibes in there.  Check it out
Burger had texture of play-doh and tasted like actual nothing. Beer was full priced and was 12 ounces - insane.

Local spot serving cocktails and bar food with a retro vibe. This is a good bar to come to with a few friends for a drink.

I stopped in here for lunch to try the burger and it far exceeded my expectations. It was juicy, seasoned, and had a tasty sauce on top. The patties were not quite smash burgers but not overly thick like many restaurant burgers are. It was a perfect size and the fries were delicious, with a double fried crisp.

Staff was rude, particularly a blonde waitress we had on Saturday. Treated us like a major inconvenience and ignored us most of the time we were there. I’ve actually never been treated so poorly at a restaurant or bar before, it was shocking. I recognize I brought a stroller in, but I have a newborn who needs to sleep in the stroller bassinet and this was daytime. Babies and postpartum moms are allowed to exist in society with others. Also, FWIW, our party mostly spoke Spanish so who knows. Seeing other reviews about how they treat POC. Fries were good. I actually never got a drink bc she didn’t bother asking me what I wanted, but my friends enjoyed their cocktails.

Absolutely great bar on the corner of Atlantic Ave & Henry St.

Looks like a typical diner from the outside but is, in fact, a stellar cocktail bar with great service.
Lovely bar, great environment, terrific staff :)
Too many drunk people getting rowdy
The martini is probably one of the best I’ve ever had. Perfect proportions. Haven’t tried the food but I will be back!
Best vibes. They make an effort to seat you / find you a spot, which is nice. Good drinks!
Super cocktails and good burgers too.
highly recommend the cocktails, burger and CHEESE CURDS
Tourist destination long forgotten by the locals

Awesome joint.
Cocktails- burgers- cheese curds
One of our favorite neighborhood bars. Great atmosphere, service, drinks, and food.

This is truly the place to be if you're looking for a bar in Brooklyn that still feels like your typical "neighborhood bar". The crowd is mostly local but I also saw a few international visitors. Service and drinks were good, I can recommend their White Negroni and the Shot & Beer too.

I would not consider this a safe space if you're a POC. We got a weird vibe immediately from some of the staff but chose to try to look past it and enjoy our evening. It got much worse as the night went on. Be aware that you too may experience very blatant prejudice and be treated unkindly. Unfortunately, I can't recommend this place at all for this reason.

don’t even bother with this place. the staff is so rude and offensive! went with a group for drinks on a friend’s birthday. the waitress told us we could gather in the corner and wait for seats, nobody seemed welcoming or offered us menus. eventually a waitress came over to ask if we were planning to order and we asked for menus and she asked for our ids and spent several minutes inspecting them even though everyone in our group is mid to late twenties. a couple people in our party placed our orders, then another staff member who seemed like the manager came over and asked us to leave because we were being “rude to the staff”. our first clue should have been the neon sign hanging on the wall that said “no dancing” - what a vibe kill. i would be curious to have tried the drinks because i doubt they were worth the $20 per cocktail.

We were treated horribly by the staff. There were about 10 of us and so they had us sit in one area of the bar. The waitress (older, blonde woman) was extremely rude and begrudgingly brought us menus when we asked. She physically moved one of the stools we were sitting in out of her way and then proceeded to card every one of us. She continue to be rude and push past us. I asked her if she was OK due to her aggressive behavior and she chose to put her hand on my arm. I asked her not to touch me and she removed her hand. She walked away in a huff and then proceeded to have another employee kick all of us out of the restaurant. A few of us had already ordered drinks and they said that they would cancel everything and that we needed to leave. One of the employees literally stood and watched us leave. It was a humiliating and uncomfortable experience. We are a very diverse group and felt that they were treating us poorly since the moment that we walked in. Very disappointing.
